22
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:04,612
这个地方今日有个名字 并且在地图上有迹可寻
This land has a name today and is marked on maps.

23
00:08:05,956 --> 00:08:10,054
但是这地名、地标、土地 全都是靠赢来的
But the names and the marks and the land all had to be won.

24
00:08:10,796 --> 00:08:13,493
从大自然和土著手上赢得的
Won from nature and from primitive man.

25
00:08:15,003 --> 00:08:19,499
五个世代之前 差不多一百二十五年前…
Five generations ago, a mere 125 years back...

26
00:08:20,812 --> 00:08:23,008
大家只称这片土地为“西部”
...this land was known only as the West...

27
00:08:24,017 --> 00:08:26,646
只有少数几个白人才知道这里
...known only to a handful of white men...

28
00:08:27,589 --> 00:08:31,652
孤单的捕兽皮者在这片 广阔荒原里寻找海狸
...lonely trappers wandering its vastness in search of beaver.

29
00:08:32,497 --> 00:08:35,661
这些人被称为山中居民 一群新世代的人
They were known as "mountain men", a new breed.

30
00:08:35,736 --> 00:08:40,004
像吉姆布里哲 法兰屈瑞和萨柏特，奈勒斯罗林等人
Men like Jim Bridger, Linus Rawlings...

31
00:08:40,810 --> 00:08:43,780
比印地安人更像印地安人 只差没印地安血统
...more Indian than the Indians in all but blood.

32
00:08:44,283 --> 00:08:46,844
他们自订法律…
They held to no law but their own...

33
00:08:47,588 --> 00:08:52,584
浮云游子，居无定所 永远不停地随处迁移
...drifted free as the clouds, settled nowhere, kept forever on the move.

34
00:08:53,230 --> 00:08:57,828
带着长满茧的双足和未钉铁鞋的马 从不驻足于任何地方
Their mocassined feet and unshod horses left no trace on the land.

35
00:09:00,574 --> 00:09:03,203
他们与那些和平相处的印地安人一样…
Like the Indians, with whom they were at peace...

36
00:09:03,646 --> 00:09:07,014
他们除了自己找到的东西之外 其他什么都不要
...they wanted nothing beyond what they found and little of that.

37
00:09:08,654 --> 00:09:12,251
群山…森林…荒野…
The mountains, the forests, the harsh country...

38
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:15,829
对他们而言，就像星星一样…
...were as unchanging to them as the stars...

39
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,227
永远都不会改变
...and just as unyielding.

40
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:24,300
在那群山和广阔平原遥遥之外…
Far behind the mountains, beyond the rolling plains...

41
00:09:25,113 --> 00:09:27,605
他们离开了东部
...they had left the people of the East...

42
00:09:27,951 --> 00:09:30,819
那些庸庸碌碌的人们
...people who were restless in another way.

43
00:09:31,323 --> 00:09:32,237
（通往西部之关卡 伊利运河）

44
00:09:32,238 --> 00:09:34,908
当他们看到高山时 便想到分水岭
The kind who would look at the mountain and see a watershed...

45
00:09:34,999 --> 00:09:36,995
看到森林时 便想到用来盖屋子的木头
...look at the forest and see lumber for houses...

46
00:09:37,065 --> 00:09:39,762
看到石头平原便想到农场
...look at a stony field and see a farm.

47
00:09:40,671 --> 00:09:43,869
他们一心一意朝向西部迈进…
Their faces and their instincts had been turned to the West...

48
00:09:44,644 --> 00:09:47,079
打从清教徒初次登陆美国之后
...ever since Plymouth Rock and James Town.

49
00:09:47,916 --> 00:09:51,649
捕兽皮者跟随狼的行迹 或峡谷弯处前进…
The trapper's road was the trade of the wolf or the bend of the canyon.

50
00:09:52,123 --> 00:09:57,188
但是携家带眷浩浩荡荡 追日前进…就必须有更宽阔的大路
But for whole families following the sun, there had to be broader ways.

52
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:02,060
但前进荒野没有陆路，只有水路
There were no roads into the woodlands, only rivers...

53
00:10:03,241 --> 00:10:06,268
结果他们便跑错方向 要不往北，就是往南
...and they flowed in the wrong direction, north or south.

54
00:10:06,412 --> 00:10:09,143
或者被挡在阿勒格尼山脚下
Or else they stopped at the Alleghanys.

55
00:10:10,050 --> 00:10:11,312
直到有天
Until one day...

56
00:10:11,921 --> 00:10:16,121
有个人发现一条新河流 这个人叫做度威克林顿
...a new river took source in the mind of a man named DeWitt Clinton.

57
00:10:16,995 --> 00:10:19,692
他认为这条河流能通往西部
He conceived of a river that would go west.

58
00:10:20,267 --> 00:10:24,865
结果美国人拿出他们冒险患难的精神 证实果然没错
And in the way Americans have of acting out their dreams, it came to be.

59
00:10:25,876 --> 00:10:28,641
伊利运河从艾柏尼之上 离开赫德森…
The Erie Canal left the Hudson above Albany...

60
00:10:28,713 --> 00:10:31,148
然后流通到五大湖
...and carried clear across to the Great Lakes.

61
00:10:32,386 --> 00:10:35,720
那些向往开垦处女地 展开新生活的人们…
People who yearned for virgin land and the new life...

62
00:10:35,991 --> 00:10:39,659
现在有一条快速水路带领他们  许多人络绎不绝
...now had a highway to take them. And they moved along.

64
00:10:40,098 --> 00:10:42,363
《乌提卡之光号》开始登船！
Pride of Utica now loading.

65
00:10:43,237 --> 00:10:46,264
（码头处）搭《乌提卡之光号》的人请登船！
All aboard for the Pride of Utica.

67
00:10:47,243 --> 00:10:50,441
兰姆西一家！ 彼得史密斯！
The Ramsey family, Peter Smith...

68
00:10:51,082 --> 00:10:53,142
史寇卡一家！
...the Skoga family...

69
00:10:53,487 --> 00:10:55,217
全部八个人！
...all eight of 'em.

70
00:10:55,790 --> 00:10:59,022
所有人请登上《乌提卡之光号》！
All aboard for the Pride of Utica.

71
00:11:01,765 --> 00:11:04,735
因为你们家儿子的健康 才会想搬去西部？
Is the laddie's health the reason you're heading west?

72
00:11:04,770 --> 00:11:05,896
有一部分是
Partly.

73
00:11:05,939 --> 00:11:08,909
我们大部分原因是 东部的土地太多石头了
Only partly. Mostly our trouble East was rocks.

74
00:11:09,245 --> 00:11:12,739
几年前我有一个农场 一亩地挖出一百桶石头
I had me a farm where some years I'd raise 100 bushels of rocks a year.

75
00:11:12,783 --> 00:11:15,218
齐伯伦，你别乱骗人家
Zebulon, you hadn't oughta lie to the man like that.

76
00:11:15,287 --> 00:11:18,724
老婆，我可是老实人 我告诉他的都是实话
Wife, I'm a God-fearing soul, and I tell the truth as I see it.

77
00:11:19,327 --> 00:11:22,856
我从来不使用锄犁 我都拿火药炸出犁沟
I never used a plow. I'd blast out the furrows with gunpowder.

78
00:11:22,933 --> 00:11:24,161
结果有天早上
Then one mornin'...

79
00:11:24,234 --> 00:11:26,169
我把桶子从井里舀上来…
...I hauled the bucket up out of the well and...

80
00:11:26,238 --> 00:11:28,935
结果那桶子里居然满满都是石头
...so help me, the bucket was full of rocks.

81
00:11:29,009 --> 00:11:29,998
石头！
Rocks.

82
00:11:30,177 --> 00:11:33,306
我站在那里 试图不口出秽言
I just stood there right still trying not to blaspheme...

83
00:11:33,483 --> 00:11:36,009
我对自己说 “你儿子身体不好”
...and said to myself: "You've got a son that's ailin'.

84
00:11:36,086 --> 00:11:38,487
“一个不肯出嫁的女儿”
"You've got a 20-year-old daughter who won't take a husband."

85
00:11:38,524 --> 00:11:40,322
- 在那里，成天幻想做梦
There she sits, moonin' as usual.

86
00:11:40,427 --> 00:11:41,189
- 爸
Pa.

87
00:11:41,295 --> 00:11:44,265
“另一个女儿脑子不晓得在想什么”
"You've got another daughter, just don't seem quite right in the head."

88
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:45,322
莉莉丝？
Lilith.

89
00:11:48,139 --> 00:11:49,197
什么事，爸？
Yes, Pa?

90
00:11:51,144 --> 00:11:52,441
我告诉你啊…
I remind you, sir.

91
00:11:53,180 --> 00:11:56,378
我站在那里 手中仍提着那装满石头的桶子…
I'm still standing there holding a bucket full of rocks...

92
00:11:57,219 --> 00:11:59,950
