00:15:58,567 --> 00:16:01,298
“他连续三次都将刀子射中目标
"Three times he hurled the knife on target.

167
00:16:01,872 --> 00:16:04,535
第一次他说代表幸运”
"'That was for luck', he said the first time.

168
00:16:04,577 --> 00:16:07,911
“第二次刺中他说代表着深刻的 神圣的爱情”
"'That was for love, deep, divine love', he said the second.

169
00:16:08,416 --> 00:16:10,977
“第三次代表着祈求一份
"And the third time, 'That was a prayer...

170
00:16:11,488 --> 00:16:13,514
永远不消逝的爱情”
"'...a plea for love undying."'

171
00:16:14,292 --> 00:16:16,193
是不是很美呢？
Isn't that beautiful?

172
00:16:17,263 --> 00:16:19,698
是啊，如果真有人那样讲话的话
I reckon. If anybody ever talks like that.

173
00:16:20,736 --> 00:16:23,262
重点是在感觉，不是那些话语
Well, it's the sentiments, not the talk.

174
00:16:23,841 --> 00:16:25,776
你真的很奇怪耶，伊芙…
There ain't no sense to you, Eve.

175
00:16:25,844 --> 00:16:29,441
你想当农夫老婆 但你却不肯嫁给农夫
You want to be a farm wife but you don't want to marry a farmer.

176
00:16:29,783 --> 00:16:31,341
你也一样啊
Neither do you.

177
00:16:31,786 --> 00:16:32,980
我当然不要
Of course not.

178
00:16:33,222 --> 00:16:35,691
我才不要和农场扯上任何关系
I don't want to have nothin' to do with farms.

179
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:38,286
我要穿丝绸衣裳，坐华丽马车
I want silk dresses and fine carriages...

180
00:16:38,463 --> 00:16:40,295
和一个味道高尚的男人
...and a man to smell good.

181
00:16:40,868 --> 00:16:43,429
我想回东部，不是去西部
What I want's back East, not West...

182
00:16:44,039 --> 00:16:46,474
我总有一天会去的，你看着好了
...and I'll get there yet. You watch.

183
00:16:46,843 --> 00:16:48,869
你根本还不晓得自己要什么
You don't know what you want yet.

184
00:16:49,648 --> 00:16:52,311
重点在于男人的特质 不是他住的地方
It's the man that counts, not where he lives.

185
00:17:00,265 --> 00:17:02,393
- 准备好了吗？ - 准备好了
-Ready, man? -Ready.

186
00:17:37,123 --> 00:17:39,718
爸爸！有人从下游来了
Daddy, somethin' comin' up river.

187
00:17:39,894 --> 00:17:41,829
我猜是具敌意的印地安人
Hostile Indians, I expect.

188
00:18:03,597 --> 00:18:06,032
- 会不会是河上海盗，齐伯伦？ - 不晓得
-Could it be river pirates, Zebulon? -Don't know.

189
00:18:07,003 --> 00:18:09,131
听说正当的人不会在夜里 航行于这条河上
They say no honest man travels this river at night.

190
00:18:09,374 --> 00:18:11,069
我只看到一个人，爸
I can only see one man, Pa.

191
00:18:11,443 --> 00:18:14,743
听说那是海盗的惯用技俩 他们都躲在船里…
I hear that's a favorite pirate trick. They hide in the bottom of the boat...

192
00:18:14,815 --> 00:18:16,579
等到接近时才发动突击
...till they're ready to jump you.

193
00:18:16,652 --> 00:18:18,917
- 去拿枪，柯林 - 好的，爸
-Get my gun, Colin. -All right, Pa.

194
00:18:27,068 --> 00:18:29,435
慢慢地靠近，陌生人
Just come in slow and easy, stranger.

195
00:18:29,973 --> 00:18:32,465
把双手放在我们看得到的地方
And keep your hands where we can see 'em.

196
00:18:50,238 --> 00:18:51,865
我叫奈勒斯罗林
Name's Linus Rawlings.

197
00:18:52,074 --> 00:18:54,635
我肚子饿坏了 我绝无恶意
I'm hungrier than sin and real peaceful like.

198
00:18:55,012 --> 00:18:57,174
- 你船上是什么东西？ - 海狸皮毛
-What've you got in the craft? -Beaver pelts.

199
00:18:57,450 --> 00:18:59,111
我说过是海狸皮毛
I said beaver pelts.

200
00:19:00,020 --> 00:19:02,990
我从没见过海狸皮毛 罗林先生
I never had a chance to see a beaver pelt, Mr. Rawlings.

201
00:19:04,928 --> 00:19:07,489
那样的话，小姐 我拿一个给你看
Well, in that case, ma'am, I'll show you one.

202
00:19:08,166 --> 00:19:09,599
你看
There you are.

203
00:19:10,169 --> 00:19:12,001
好软喔
Oh, that's real soft.

204
00:19:12,506 --> 00:19:13,734
这可是上等皮毛，小姐
It's a fine pelt, ma'am.

205
00:19:13,808 --> 00:19:15,800
真对不起，先生
Now, my apologies, sir.

206
00:19:16,713 --> 00:19:18,682
- 我们原先还担心你是海盗
We was afraid you might be a pirate.

207
00:19:18,850 --> 00:19:19,908
我才不是海盗
I ain't no pirate.

208
00:19:19,985 --> 00:19:22,682
来吧，咱们一起吃晚饭 多认识认识
Come on, let's have supper and get acquainted.

209
00:19:23,557 --> 00:19:26,152
不用了，送你 你留着，小姐
No, no. That's yours. You keep that.

210
00:19:42,019 --> 00:19:44,181
你动作还真快
Well, you sure set your cap in a hurry.

211
00:19:44,257 --> 00:19:46,783
他是不是你一直在等的 砍柴樵夫呢？
Is he the backwoodsman you've been waiting for?

212
00:19:46,860 --> 00:19:50,092
我看他八成有个老婆和六个孩子 在家里等着他呢
More than likely he's got a wife and six kids waiting for him.

213
00:19:54,773 --> 00:19:57,334
"When I was single

214
00:19:58,779 --> 00:20:01,578
"Went dressed up so fine

215
00:20:03,052 --> 00:20:05,954
"Now I am married

216
00:20:07,226 --> 00:20:10,594
"Go ragged all the time."

217
00:20:15,973 --> 00:20:18,272
谢谢你，小姐 真的太好吃了
Thank you, ma'am, that was right tasty.

218
00:20:18,310 --> 00:20:21,873
你才吃四盘 我一开始还以为你不喜欢吃呢
You've only ate four plates. I was beginning to think you didn't like it.

219
00:20:21,949 --> 00:20:25,249
空腹一开始吃不了太多，小姐
Well, it don't pay to eat too much on an empty stomach, ma'am.

220
00:20:26,189 --> 00:20:28,750
你为什么这么晚还在旅行？
How come you to be travelin' so late at night?

221
00:20:28,826 --> 00:20:30,988
因为我很想赶快去匹兹堡
Well, I'm kinda anxious to get to Pittsburgh.

222
00:20:31,064 --> 00:20:34,797
我已经很久没见到大城市 我想赶路快点到达
I ain't seen a city for a long time. I aim to whoop it up a little.

223
00:20:35,972 --> 00:20:38,271
我们从未见过山中居民
We've never seen a mountain man before.

224
00:20:38,342 --> 00:20:41,278
告诉我，洛矶山脉真有人家说的 那么高吗？
Tell me, them Rocky Mountains as high as they say?

225
00:20:42,014 --> 00:20:45,143
这个…我也不是很清楚 我从来没爬上去过，我…
Well, now, I just don't rightly know. I never climbed one.

226
00:20:49,994 --> 00:20:52,657
不过呢…那也不尽然啦…
I've, well...that just ain't exactly true.

227
00:20:53,399 --> 00:20:57,895
吉姆布里哲和我…我们一开始先爬
Jim Bridger and me, we started up one of them little biddy...

228
00:20:55,171 --> 00:21:00,259


229
00:20:57,972 --> 00:21:00,806
洛矶山脚下的一座小山
...Rocky Mountain foothills, you know.

230
00:21:01,144 --> 00:21:04,342
结果有一天 我们遇到一个人…
And then, one day, we see this fella...

231
00:21:05,117 --> 00:21:08,714
他有一对巨大的白色翅膀…
...and he has a great big pair of white wings...

232
00:21:09,691 --> 00:21:11,249
手里还抱着竖琴
...and a harp in his hand.

233
00:21:12,094 --> 00:21:13,721
我便对吉姆说…
And I said to Jim...

234
00:21:14,165 --> 00:21:17,796
“吉姆，我不喜欢这个人 看我们的样子”
...I said, "Jim, I don't like the way that fella's lookin' at us."

235
00:21:18,071 --> 00:21:22,032
然后吉姆说他也不是很喜欢…
And Jim said he didn't care too much for it either...

236
00:21:22,377 --> 00:21:24,710
结果我们便赶紧溜下山离开了
...so we both skidaddled down out of there...

237
00:21:24,748 --> 00:21:28,743
直到今天 我从来没好好看过洛矶山一眼
...and to this day I ain't never had a good look at the Rocky Mountains.

238
00:21:35,165 --> 00:21:36,689
- 我记得有一次… - 齐伯伦
-I remember one time-- -Zebulon.

239
00:21:36,767 --> 00:21:37,392
- 怎样？
What?

240
00:21:37,435 --> 00:21:39,870
一次一个人吹牛已经够了
One liar at a time is enough.

241
00:21:41,842 --> 00:21:44,243
现在差不多该睡觉了
Well, then, I reckon it's about bedtime.

242
00:21:44,746 --> 00:21:46,304
明天还得早起赶路呢
Gotta get an early start in the mornin'.

243
00:21:46,415 --> 00:21:48,247
我们一起吃早餐，罗林先生
We'll be expectin' you for breakfast.

244
00:21:48,318 --> 00:21:50,810
喔，你真是太客气了 普莱斯考特先生
Well, that's mighty hospitable, Mr. Prescott...

245
00:21:50,890 --> 00:21:52,984
我经常一醒过来就要马上赶路
...but sometimes I wake up and get the urge to move.

246
00:21:53,059 --> 00:21:55,722
日出之前我大概早就出发了 多谢你的邀请
I might be long gone by sunup, but I want to thank you.

247
00:21:55,898 --> 00:21:57,833
- 非常感谢各位，晚安
I want to thank all of you. Good night.

248
00:21:57,901 --> 00:21:58,959
- 晚安
Good night.

249
00:22:00,805 --> 00:22:02,831
- 这些山中居民可真不寻常
Strange fellas, these mountain men.

250
00:22:02,909 --> 00:22:05,344
- 是啊，来去有如一阵烟
Yeah, kind of like a wisp of smoke.

251
00:22:25,210 --> 00:22:27,338
- 哇！那看起来好像我的毯子
By golly, that looks like my blanket.

252
00:22:27,414 --> 00:22:28,403
- 是你的毯子没错
It is.

253
00:22:28,549 --> 00:22:32,078
那我可就糊涂了，小姐 这床是给谁睡的呢？
Well, then, I'm a might confused, ma'am. Whose bed would it be?

254
00:22:32,155 --> 00:22:33,144
给你睡的
Yours.

255
00:22:34,825 --> 00:22:38,388
打从我离开东岸之后 再也没看过这样的床
I ain't never saw a bed like that since last time I come East.

256
00:22:39,533 --> 00:22:41,000
你为什么要帮我？
Why'd you do it?

257
00:22:41,569 --> 00:22:45,063
问一个女孩为什么帮一个男人做事 是不礼貌的
It ain't polite to ask a girl why she done something for a man.

258
00:22:45,442 --> 00:22:48,241
是啊，我的言行的确有些失礼
No. Well, I reckon my manners ain't much at that.

259
00:22:48,347 --> 00:22:50,873
不过，我倒是很感谢你 晚安，小姐
Anyway, I sure thank you. Good night, ma'am.

260
00:22:56,860 --> 00:22:58,487
那些印地安女孩漂亮吗？
Are them Indian girls pretty?

261
00:22:58,863 --> 00:23:02,528
我认为这得视男人到底有多久…
Well, now, I reckon that all depends on just how long a man's gone...

262
00:23:02,836 --> 00:23:04,303
没看到女人而定
...without seein' one.

263
00:23:05,574 --> 00:23:08,237
你有多久没看到白人女孩？
How long's it been since you seen a white girl?

264
00:23:09,246 --> 00:23:11,613
我不确定你为什么这么问
I ain't quite sure why you asked that.

265
00:23:14,121 --> 00:23:16,090
你觉得我有多漂亮？
How pretty do I look to you?

266
00:23:15,811 --> 00:23:17,479
小姐…

267
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:20,852
你这样不会太开放了吧？
Ain't you just bein' a little bit forward?

268
00:23:21,483 --> 00:23:26,572


269
00:23:23,535 --> 00:23:26,232
你往上游走 我要往下游走
You're headed upriver and I'm headed down.

270
00:23:27,242 --> 00:23:29,609
没有太多时间可以听你的回答
There's no time to get these questions answered.

271
00:23:32,517 --> 00:23:35,043
你确定你想听我的回答？
You dead sure you want 'em answered?

272
00:23:37,123 --> 00:23:38,112
是的
Yes.

273
00:23:52,114 --> 00:23:53,274
老天…
Oh, glory be!

274
00:23:55,419 --> 00:23:57,945
小姐，你好像从前曾经亲吻过
Ma'am, it seems like you've been kissed before.

275
00:24:00,260 --> 00:24:02,525
我从未永久性地被亲吻过
I've never been kissed permanent before.

276
00:24:03,999 --> 00:24:06,332
哇，你用字遣词真特别
By golly, you sure use surprising words.

277
00:24:06,403 --> 00:24:10,307
我从没听过有人把“永久性”和 吻这玩意摆在一起形容
I never heard permanent mixed up with a thing like a kiss before.

278
00:24:12,246 --> 00:24:14,181
我仍能感受到那份吻
I can still feel that kiss.

279
00:24:14,983 --> 00:24:15,711
- 你能吗？
Can you?

280
00:24:15,952 --> 00:24:18,717
- 你刚才讲了一句话…我还没忘记…
You said somethin' before we hadn't oughta forget:

281
00:24:18,990 --> 00:24:22,358
我要往上游走 你要往下游走
I'm headin' upstream and you're headed downstream.

282
00:24:23,463 --> 00:24:26,331
曾经分离过的情人终将再度聚首 - 小姐 - 叫我伊芙
Lovers have parted before and come together again.

283
00:24:25,422 --> 00:24:26,882


284
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:32,410
伊芙，我是个罪孽深重的人
Eve, I, I'm a sinful man.

285
00:24:34,447 --> 00:24:36,416
一个万劫不复的罪人
I'm deep, dark, sinful.

286
00:24:36,518 --> 00:24:39,386
我正要前往匹兹堡再度当个罪人
I'm on my way to Pittsburgh to be sinful again.

287
00:24:40,557 --> 00:24:42,423
我有可能会酒醉一个月
Likely I'll stay drunk for a month.

288
00:24:42,493 --> 00:24:45,429
我将不会记得我泡过的女人…
I won't even remember the fancy gals I dally with...

289
00:24:45,498 --> 00:24:48,434
或出自意气用事打过架的男人…
...or the men I carve up just out of pure cussedness...

290
00:24:48,503 --> 00:24:50,495
更别说是记得你这个人
...any more than I'll remember you.

291
00:24:52,075 --> 00:24:55,409
奈勒斯，我问你 你是否仍感觉到刚才那个吻？
Linus, I'm askin' you. Can you still feel that kiss?

292
00:24:56,782 --> 00:24:58,010
伊芙…
Eve....

293
00:25:00,054 --> 00:25:04,493
伊芙，你让我感觉好像 踮着脚站在一道窄路上…
Eve, you make me feel like a man standing on a narrow ledge...

294
00:25:05,196 --> 00:25:07,791
迎面挑战一头恶狠狠的大熊
...comin' face to face with a grizzly bear.

295
00:25:09,770 --> 00:25:13,401
我根本无法不去面对那处境
There just ain't no ignorin' the situation.

296
00:25:35,344 --> 00:25:36,743
伊芙！
Eve!

297
00:25:42,688 --> 00:25:44,383
- 伊芙！她人呢？ - 齐伯，怎么回事？
Eve! Where is she?

298
00:25:45,325 --> 00:25:47,760
你在就好 我以为你和他走了
Anyways, you're here. I thought you'd gone with him.

299
00:25:48,364 --> 00:25:50,333
- 走了？ - 是的，走了
-Gone? -Yes, gone.

300
00:25:51,702 --> 00:25:53,728
我就知道你喜欢他…
I knowed you were settin' with him...

301
00:25:54,140 --> 00:25:56,905
但我一直告诉自己 “至少她喜欢男人”
...but I kept tellin' myself at least she's lookin' at a man.

302
00:25:57,144 --> 00:25:59,739
即便像那种一阵烟的男人也好
Even a wisp of smoke like that is better than--

303
00:26:02,887 --> 00:26:06,221
你在哭？为他哭？ 这是什么意思？
Are you cryin'? Cryin' for him? Now, what does that mean?

304
00:26:07,360 --> 00:26:09,261
告诉我这是什么意思？
Now, tell me what that means.

305
00:26:10,532 --> 00:26:11,692
没什么意思，爸
Nothin', Pa.

306
00:26:12,302 --> 00:26:13,929
你几点上床睡觉的？
What time did you come to bed?

307
00:26:14,773 --> 00:26:16,263
很早就睡了，爸
It was early, Pa.

308
00:26:17,410 --> 00:26:19,140
不…很晚
It wasn't. It was late.

309
00:26:20,214 --> 00:26:22,479
女儿啊，我只问你一次…
Daughter, I'm only gonna ask you once.

310
00:26:22,785 --> 00:26:25,755
有没有任何事情是值得 你妈和我担心的？
Is there anything for your ma and pa to worry about?

311
00:26:26,858 --> 00:26:28,382
没有，爸，没事
No, Pa, there ain't.

312
00:26:45,754 --> 00:26:47,187
他会再回来的
He'll be back.

313
00:26:48,192 --> 00:26:49,557
我会再见到他的
I'll see him again.

314
00:26:49,728 --> 00:26:52,926
但你原本以为今天早上会见到他 你是这么想的
But you expected to see him this morning. You know you did.

315
00:26:53,633 --> 00:26:55,761
我不管，我会再见到他的
I don't care. I'll see him again.

316
00:26:57,306 --> 00:26:58,330
你看…
Look.

317
00:27:04,784 --> 00:27:06,810
- 你让一个大男人为你这么做？
You got a growed man to do that?

318
00:27:06,955 --> 00:27:09,322
- 没错，就像书里写的一样
I did, just like in the book.

319
00:27:10,627 --> 00:27:12,960
你有让他对你说那些疯狂的话吗？
Did you get him to say them crazy words?

320
00:27:13,866 --> 00:27:17,234
我说过了，重点不在那些话 而是那种感觉
I told you before, it ain't the words, it's the sentiment.

321
00:27:18,005 --> 00:27:21,602
你是说他没有笑那些无聊的事？
You mean he didn't even giggle or nothin' at such foolishness?

322
00:27:22,579 --> 00:27:24,912
他说那是很严肃的一件事
He said it was a real solemn occasion...

323
00:27:25,918 --> 00:27:28,649
好像在急流中不用划板一样
...like shootin' the rapids without a paddle.

324
00:27:30,658 --> 00:27:34,562
不管他怎么说，他这么做只是为了 打发你好赶紧脱身
No matter what he said, he did it just to get rid of you so as he could clear out.

325
00:27:34,632 --> 00:27:35,997
你知道是这样没错的
You know that's so.

326
00:27:37,002 --> 00:27:40,906
算你走运他那么做 你真打算懵懵懂懂过一辈子？
And you're lucky he did. Do you want to live like a squaw all your life?

327
00:27:40,974 --> 00:27:43,034
随便你想说什么都行
Go on, say anything you like...

328
00:27:43,679 --> 00:27:46,080
我一定会再见到他的 我知道我会的
...but I'll see him again. I know I will.

329
00:27:46,784 --> 00:27:48,980
而且他才没有老婆 也没有六个孩子
And he ain't got a wife and six kids.

330
00:27:49,688 --> 00:27:51,680
他还没讨老婆呢！
He ain't got a wife at all yet.

331
00:28:03,181 --> 00:28:04,725
（贩卖酒品 杰布霍金斯）

332
00:28:05,814 --> 00:28:08,682
嘿，皮耶！有人从上游来了
Pierre, someone's comin' upriver.

333
00:28:06,768 --> 00:28:08,103


334
00:28:23,775 --> 00:28:24,833
有客人来了！
Customer.

335
00:28:33,758 --> 00:28:36,853
好像是捕兽皮者  瞧那鼓鼓的一团？
Trapper, seems like. See how that cover bellies up?

336
00:28:34,838 --> 00:28:38,759


337
00:28:37,430 --> 00:28:38,863
有可能是皮毛
Could be furs.

338
00:28:51,119 --> 00:28:52,552
口渴吗，先生？
Thirsty, mister?

339
00:28:52,888 --> 00:28:56,154
比热锅上的蚱蜢还要渴
Drier than a grasshopper on a hot griddle.

340
00:28:59,766 --> 00:29:02,031
那么，欢迎您光临我们的小旅舍
Well, welcome to our little inn, sir.

341
00:29:02,571 --> 00:29:05,564
我叫杰布霍金斯 曾经是阿拉巴马州的国民军上校
My name is Jeb Hawkins, late colonel of the Alabama militia.

342
00:29:05,641 --> 00:29:06,972
- 你要去哪？ - 匹兹堡
-Where you bound for? -Pittsburgh.

343
00:29:07,044 --> 00:29:08,409
匹兹堡？
Pittsburgh?

344
00:29:08,479 --> 00:29:11,040
他好像有一整船的皮毛呢，爸
Looks like he's got a whole canoe of furs, Pop.

345
00:29:11,418 --> 00:29:13,614
- 一定是个山中居民 - 没错
-A sure enough mountain man. -Indeed.

346
00:29:13,654 --> 00:29:17,422
咱们的探险家开疆辟土前进到 遥远的太平洋海岸
One of our brave explorers gonna extend our domain to the far shores of the Pacific.

347
00:29:17,493 --> 00:29:19,689
一定要请你喝最上等的酒 威士忌？
Nothin' but the finest for you, sir. Whiskey?

348
00:29:19,764 --> 00:29:20,753
- 好的
Right.

349
00:29:20,865 --> 00:29:22,629
- 这里面没加胡椒或响尾蛇
No pepper or rattlesnake heads in this.

350
00:29:22,702 --> 00:29:24,967
除了甜美的麦芽啥都没乱加
Nothin' but the pure grain and the sweet kiss of the malt.

351
00:29:25,006 --> 00:29:27,601
- 不必用杯子，我直接整罐喝了
Never mind the cup, I'll just take the jug.

352
00:29:28,645 --> 00:29:30,112
- 喔，真正的山中居民
A real mountain man, eh?

353
00:29:30,181 --> 00:29:32,047
- 你为国旗敬一杯吧！
I trust you'll toast our noble banner, sir.

354
00:29:32,117 --> 00:29:33,550
- 那当然
I sure will.

355
00:29:54,953 --> 00:29:57,184
你说得没错 这果然是上等好酒
Golly, you're right. That's real sippin' liquor.

356
00:29:57,223 --> 00:29:58,485
爸，既然他是捕兽皮者
Pa, him being a trapper...

357
00:29:58,558 --> 00:30:01,050
你想他会知道我们抓到的是什么野兽？
...do you suppose he might know what that varmint is we got?

358
00:30:01,129 --> 00:30:03,997
或许吧…我想他应该会晓得
Well, say, now, he might. Yes, sir, he just might.

359
00:30:04,100 --> 00:30:06,501
我们抓到一只穴居野兽…
Sir, we catched us a cave-dwellin' critter...

360
00:30:06,571 --> 00:30:08,563
在我们从没去过的地方抓到的
...that no man in these parts has ever seen before.

361
00:30:08,675 --> 00:30:12,204
如果你能告诉我们 那到底是什么玩意就太好了
And, you know, it'd be right satisfyin' havin' you tell us what it is.

362
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:15,717
我对穴居野兽不太了解
Well, I don't know too much about cave-dwellin' varmints.

363
00:30:16,253 --> 00:30:18,586
就在这附近 把你的酒带着
Just yonder, take your jug.

364
00:30:19,443 --> 00:30:21,653


365
00:30:24,232 --> 00:30:25,665
这个…我… 我不知道…
I don't know....

366
00:30:43,129 --> 00:30:44,653
就在这里
It's right over here.

367
00:30:55,648 --> 00:30:57,879
你在匹兹堡有没有女朋友？
You know any sweet-talkin' girls in Pittsburgh?

368
00:30:57,952 --> 00:30:59,921
没有…一个都没有…还没
No, nary a one, yet.

369
00:31:00,823 --> 00:31:03,156
我和爸正考虑去那里度假呢
Pop and I are hopin' we'll vacation there.

370
00:31:03,227 --> 00:31:06,254
我会在《杜肯酒店》 如果还没被烧掉的话
I'll be at the Duquesne House if it ain't burned down.

371
00:31:07,334 --> 00:31:08,801
嘿…
Hey there, now....

372
00:31:09,237 --> 00:31:13,039
小美女… 你确定你的野兽关在这里？
You pretty girl, you sure you got a varmint in here?

373
00:31:13,330 --> 00:31:14,790


374
00:31:15,814 --> 00:31:17,145
你有听到吗？
Do you hear him?

375
00:31:17,417 --> 00:31:19,352
它的呼吸声又大又猛
He breathes loud and fierce.

376
00:31:20,120 --> 00:31:23,649
- 我们把它关在那边的洞里 - 你们把它关在这里？
-We keep him in this hole just yonder. -You keep him in there?

377
00:31:26,297 --> 00:31:28,163
你得再靠近点看
You gotta look a little closer.

378
00:31:48,766 --> 00:31:50,701
他看到野兽了，爸
Well, he seed the varmint, Pa.

379
00:31:50,735 --> 00:31:51,827
- 干得好 女儿
Well done, daughter.

380
00:31:51,904 --> 00:31:53,303
- 我不太确定…
I ain't so sure.

381
00:31:53,740 --> 00:31:57,177
他的肌肉结实 我可以感觉到他的肋骨锐利如刀片
He was hard-muscled. I could feel the blade just kinda skitter along his ribs.

382
00:31:57,246 --> 00:31:59,442
喔，你只需要多练习几次 没什么
You just need more practice, that's all.

383
00:31:59,683 --> 00:32:02,084
真可惜你没有你妈的绝招
It's a pity you ain't got the knack your ma had...

384
00:32:02,153 --> 00:32:03,814
祝她安息
...Lord rest her soul.

385
00:32:04,324 --> 00:32:05,348
好吧，各位，快行动吧
All right, men....

386
00:32:05,425 --> 00:32:06,483
快点！快点！
Lay into it, men.

387
00:32:06,727 --> 00:32:09,697
咱们去大赚一票！
Come on, we've got a lot of fish to fry.

388
00:32:09,866 --> 00:32:11,231
到岛上去！
Down to the island.

389
00:33:08,825 --> 00:33:11,386
通知爸爸拓荒者的船来了
Tell Pa them settlers' rafts are comin'.

390
00:33:14,826 --> 00:33:17,829
（贝罗商店 供需品及以货易货）

391
00:33:29,633 --> 00:33:31,551
（贝罗商店 还缺什么吗？）

392
00:33:31,718 --> 00:33:33,178
（匹兹堡价钱）

393
00:33:36,102 --> 00:33:38,003
我可以买这瓶香水吗，爸？
Can't I have this toilet water, Pa?

394
00:33:38,071 --> 00:33:40,973
- 是原装巴黎香水呢 - 多少钱？
-Genuine Parisian Accent, it says. -How much is it?

395
00:33:41,210 --> 00:33:42,837
只要一毛五
It's only 15 cents.

396
00:33:42,979 --> 00:33:44,845
一毛五？给我放回去
Fifteen cents! Put it back.

397
00:33:44,915 --> 00:33:49,183
是啊，没错 省几毛钱，几块钱便因运而生
You're right, sir. Absolutely right. You save the pennies and dollars will grow.

398
00:33:49,255 --> 00:33:51,247
钱慢慢积少成多
Likely you've growed many a dollar, ain't you?

399
00:33:51,326 --> 00:33:54,626
贝罗先生，我这一生总避免自己成为 百万富翁
Mr. Peddler, all my life I've been strivin' to avoid becomin' a millionaire...

400
00:33:54,865 --> 00:33:56,857
我目前为止还挺成功的
...and I think I've succeeded right well.

401
00:33:56,934 --> 00:33:59,495
我袜子里只有几块钱 我不会乱花的
I've got a little put away in the sock and it'll stay right there.

402
00:33:59,605 --> 00:34:02,074
我完全赞同你的说法
Well, now, them's my sentiments exactly.

403
00:34:02,209 --> 00:34:04,576
先生，你看起来倒像个有钱人
Now, you, sir-- You look like a man of property.

404
00:34:04,613 --> 00:34:08,608
若要我猜的话 我想你身价差不多一千元
Now, if I was to bet, I'd say you was worth a $1,000.

405
00:34:09,287 --> 00:34:10,379
- 是不是挺接近呢？
Pretty close to the mark?

406
00:34:10,456 --> 00:34:11,946
- 差不多，或许吧
Well, close, maybe.

407
00:35:08,013 --> 00:35:09,674
- 柯林，我们还剩下多少火药？
Colin, how much powder we got left?

408
00:35:09,749 --> 00:35:12,184
- 别害怕，别怕
Don't be afeerd, now, don't be afeerd.

409
00:35:12,219 --> 00:35:14,017
这里有女人和小孩
Now, there's women and children here.

410
00:35:14,055 --> 00:35:17,457
你们不会希望我们开枪扫射吧？
You gents wouldn't want us to have to start shootin', now, would you?

411
00:35:17,729 --> 00:35:19,493
大家冷静点
Be of good cheer, folks.

412
00:35:19,665 --> 00:35:22,430
咱们的使命是开疆辟土…
Why, it's in our noble tradition to conquer the wilderness...

413
00:35:22,502 --> 00:35:25,063
凭着我们的赤手空拳和果断的心
...with nothin' but our bare hands and stout hearts.

414
00:35:25,140 --> 00:35:29,169
你们大家可以拿出祖先的克难精神 再建造新的船筏
You can build new rafts and sally forth in the spirit of your forefathers.

415
00:35:29,280 --> 00:35:31,442
你这个不要脸的小人！
Why, you pious old scoundrel.

416
00:35:32,451 --> 00:35:34,078
你会下地狱！
I'll see you burn.

417
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:43,564
美国人不是那么好欺负的！
Americans can't be whipped.

418
00:35:44,804 --> 00:35:45,828
是他！
It's him.

419
00:35:46,273 --> 00:35:48,333
我就知道他会回来！是他！
I knew he'd come back. It's him.

420
00:36:45,366 --> 00:36:47,767
让我们一起来祈祷
Now, let us pray.

421
00:36:50,241 --> 00:36:51,401
上帝啊…
Oh, Lord...

422
00:36:53,379 --> 00:36:55,473
感谢您让我们逃过一劫
...we thank Thee for our salvation.

423
00:36:56,217 --> 00:36:59,278
我们希望将死者的灵魂交托给您
We commit the souls of our dead to Thy gentle keepin'.

424
00:37:00,557 --> 00:37:03,186
祈祷我们之中受伤的人能早日康复
We pray for a speedy recovery of our wounded.

425
00:37:06,466 --> 00:37:08,196
另外还有一件事…
And, now, another matter.

426
00:37:09,504 --> 00:37:10,562
上帝啊…
Oh, Lord...

427
00:37:11,909 --> 00:37:13,901
在未曾请教过您的情况下…
...without consulting with Thee...

428
00:37:14,612 --> 00:37:18,880
我们将几个被魔鬼缠附的灵魂 送到您那里
...we have sent Thy way some souls whose evil ways passeth all understanding.

429
00:37:20,689 --> 00:37:22,749
我们恳求您收容那些灵魂
We ask Thee humbly to receive them...

430
00:37:24,462 --> 00:37:26,431
不管您愿不愿意接受
...whether You want 'em or not.

431
00:37:26,465 --> 00:37:27,489
阿们
Amen.

432
00:37:49,702 --> 00:37:50,896
这得花点功夫修补
It'll be a job.

433
00:37:50,970 --> 00:37:54,372
我一定能把它修好 然后前去匹兹堡
But I guess I can patch her up good enough to get to Pittsburgh.

434
00:37:54,910 --> 00:37:56,468
- 奈勒斯… - 别这样，伊芙…
-Linus. -Now, Eve...

435
00:37:56,946 --> 00:37:59,438
我们别再谈这件事了
...let's just not talk any more about it.

436
00:38:00,352 --> 00:38:03,322
奈勒斯，我告诉你 你根本不懂你自己的心
Linus, I'm tellin' you, you don't know your own mind.

437
00:38:04,258 --> 00:38:05,623
或许是，或许不是
Maybe so, maybe not.

438
00:38:05,794 --> 00:38:09,254
我并不是说我没偶尔想起你
I know I ain't sayin' that you haven't been on my mind some.

439
00:38:09,566 --> 00:38:10,965
我并没那样说
I ain't sayin' that.

440
00:38:11,069 --> 00:38:14,437
但我仍和那个海盗女 一起跑去看野兽
But I still went to see the varmint with that pirate girl.

441
00:38:14,707 --> 00:38:17,472
我永远都会想要跑去看“野兽”，伊芙
I'll always be goin' to see the varmint, Eve.

442
00:38:17,979 --> 00:38:21,815
我根本不是农夫或丈夫的料
I, I just ain't cut out to be a farmer or a husband.

443
00:38:23,054 --> 00:38:25,990
奈勒斯，我再也不会提起这件事…
Linus, I ain't never bringing up the subject again...

444
00:38:26,326 --> 00:38:28,318
不管我会不会再见到你
...whether ever I see you or not.

445
00:38:28,463 --> 00:38:29,953
这对我们大家都好
Now, it's for the best.

446
00:38:31,334 --> 00:38:32,858
我希望你一切顺心，伊芙
I wish you Godspeed, Eve.

447
00:38:34,305 --> 00:38:37,834
我已经很久没对人那样说了
And I ain't said that to anybody for a long time.

448
00:39:12,598 --> 00:39:15,568
我看到前面有急流，爸 白花花的浪头
I can see rapids ahead, Pa. White water.

449
00:39:15,837 --> 00:39:17,031
你们看！
Look. Look.

450
00:39:17,373 --> 00:39:19,433
喔，我们一定走错叉路了
Oh, we must've taken the wrong fork.

451
00:39:19,509 --> 00:39:21,535
把船停靠岸！
Let's beach her on this side.

452
00:39:21,947 --> 00:39:23,141
哈维！
Harvey!

453
00:39:24,885 --> 00:39:25,943
急流！
Rapids.

454
00:39:26,621 --> 00:39:28,385
前面有急流！把船靠岸！
Rapids ahead! Beach her!

455
00:39:29,392 --> 00:39:30,484
把船靠岸！
Beach her!

456
00:39:33,999 --> 00:39:35,432
稳住船身！
Hold her steady.

457
00:39:41,477 --> 00:39:42,501
拉住！
Strain!

458
00:39:43,848 --> 00:39:45,612
爸，我们被卷进急流了！
Pa, we're in the current.

459
00:39:49,824 --> 00:39:51,121
进去里面，齐克
Get inside, Zeke.

460
00:39:52,462 --> 00:39:53,759
不！我不要！
No, I don't wanna.

461
00:40:00,207 --> 00:40:01,834
往直行，爸！
Straighten her, Pa.

462
00:40:04,046 --> 00:40:05,104
莉莉丝！
Lilith!

463
00:40:25,514 --> 00:40:26,742
稳住！
Hold it steady!

464
00:40:29,754 --> 00:40:30,743
没办法！
I can't!

465
00:41:47,643 --> 00:41:49,407
快去！快去帮爸爸！
Go on. Go on and help Pa.

466
00:41:50,681 --> 00:41:51,807
我来！
I'll get it.

467
00:42:07,942 --> 00:42:09,877
莉莉丝！莉莉丝！
Lilith! Lilith!

468
00:42:45,768 --> 00:42:47,395
趴下！
Lie down!

469
00:42:48,472 --> 00:42:49,803
趴下！
Lie down!

470
00:43:25,431 --> 00:43:26,762
怎么回事？
What happened?

471
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:30,768
他们走错河道 往瀑布冲下去了
They took the wrong fork of the river and they went over the falls.

472
00:43:30,940 --> 00:43:33,307
你可知道是哪个人家？
Did you happen to hear the name of the family?

473
00:43:33,443 --> 00:43:35,912
普莱斯考特家族，好像是他们
Prescott, I think. Something like that.

474
00:43:51,038 --> 00:43:53,132
一旦好好安葬过他们…
As soon as they're buried decent...

475
00:43:53,208 --> 00:43:56,201
我就要搭上第一艘回东部的船！
...l'm heading back East on the first boat that comes along.

476
00:43:56,313 --> 00:43:59,340
你若头脑清楚的话 你也会这么做
And if you were in your right mind, you would, too.

477
00:44:29,499 --> 00:44:30,898
喔，奈勒斯…
Oh, Linus.

478
00:44:59,479 --> 00:45:04,475
摇滚年代，离我远去
"Rock of ages, cleft for me

479
00:45:06,090 --> 00:45:11,052
让我把自己你放在心里
"Let me hide myself in thee

480
00:45:12,500 --> 00:45:17,462
让泪水和流血
"Let the water and the blood

481
00:45:18,509 --> 00:45:23,505
从此远离
"From thy side, a healing flood

482
00:45:25,086 --> 00:45:29,388
双重医治我的罪过
"Be of sin the double cure

483
00:45:31,095 --> 00:45:36,297
把我的罪恶洗净
"Cleanse me from its guilt and power."

484
00:45:55,802 --> 00:45:58,135
你陪我散步一下好吗，伊芙？
Would you walk with me a piece, Eve?

485
00:46:18,437 --> 00:46:19,495
伊芙，我…
Eve, I....

486
00:46:21,709 --> 00:46:25,340
伊芙，我刚才一路划过来时 我心里想着…
Eve, all the time I was paddlin' down here I was thinkin'...

487
00:46:27,151 --> 00:46:29,746
如果我看到你还活着 我就…
...if I found you alive, I'd--

488
00:46:31,490 --> 00:46:33,857
你愿意和我一起去匹兹堡吗，伊芙？
Would you come to Pittsburgh with me, Eve?

489
00:46:35,042 --> 00:46:37,295


490
00:46:39,337 --> 00:46:40,827
喔，奈勒斯… 我要留在这里
I'm stayin' right here.

491
00:46:41,740 --> 00:46:44,335
不管怎样我都不会离开这里一步
I ain't movin' a foot one way or the other.

492
00:46:46,514 --> 00:46:48,608
能告诉我为什么吗？
Now would you explain that a little?

493
00:46:50,754 --> 00:46:53,223
爸爸妈妈想到西部开辟一座农场…
Ma and Pa, they wanted a farm in the West...

494
00:46:54,159 --> 00:46:56,219
他们只走到这么远
...and this is as far as they got.

495
00:46:57,632 --> 00:47:00,796
我觉得这是上帝要农场搭盖的地方
Seems to me this is where the Lord wanted the farm to be.

496
00:47:01,137 --> 00:47:04,164
可是你的弟弟山姆受伤那么严重 冬天就要来了…
But your brother, Sam, he's bad hurt, and winter's comin'--

497
00:47:04,242 --> 00:47:06,643
再怎么说都没用 我非这么做不可
There's no sense talkin' about it. I'm gonna do it.

498
00:47:06,680 --> 00:47:09,172
伊芙，你这样根本不合理啊
Eve, you just ain't makin' much sense.

499
00:47:10,819 --> 00:47:14,382
我想有半数前来西部的人 都不是按牌理出牌的
Half the people that come West don't make much sense, I reckon.

500
00:47:19,633 --> 00:47:20,622
好吧
All right.

501
00:47:21,870 --> 00:47:22,859
好吧
All right.

502
00:47:25,175 --> 00:47:27,508
老天，你真是个意志坚定的女人
By golly, you're a strong-minded woman.

503
00:47:30,483 --> 00:47:33,510
我向你保证 那是我最后一次看野兽了
I reckon I seen that varmint for the last time.

504
00:48:20,764 --> 00:48:24,361
迈向西部之路并不比 追求真爱来得平顺
The westward course was no smoother than that of true love.

505
00:48:25,670 --> 00:48:29,665
不仅得面对残酷大自然的考验 另外还有战争的阻碍
Not only the hard hand of nature was against it, but the impediment of war.

506
00:48:30,311 --> 00:48:33,645
美墨边境地带一直不断出现战事
Trouble over land smoldered along the Mexican border.

507
00:48:33,884 --> 00:48:38,255
并不是所有美国人都赞成战争 包括伊利诺州的众议员亚柏林肯
Not all Americans were for war, including Congressman Abe Lincoln of Illinois.

508
00:48:38,691 --> 00:48:40,455
但战事仍爆发了 到最后…
But a war did break out...

509
00:48:40,795 --> 00:48:43,890
许多带着浓厚西班牙色彩地名的新领地
...and in the end vast new territories came into the Union...

510
00:48:43,966 --> 00:48:45,764
被纳入联邦政府的一部分…
...along with their rich Spanish names:

511
00:48:45,803 --> 00:48:49,332
里欧格蓝德…圣塔菲… 亚柏考基…艾尔帕索
Rio Grande, Santa Fe, Albuquerque, El Paso...

512
00:48:49,975 --> 00:48:52,604
还有其中最出名的是…加州
...and most glittering of all, California...

513
00:48:53,047 --> 00:48:57,679
以一本十五世纪小说里 一处充满珍珠与黄金神秘小岛为命名的
...named after a mythical island of pearls and gold in a 15th century novel.

514
00:48:57,988 --> 00:49:00,457
而现在1848年…
Here, in 1848...

515
00:49:00,893 --> 00:49:04,661
在萨特磨坊 有个人无意间在沟底处…
...at Sutter's Mill, a man found something he wasn't even looking for...

516
00:49:04,732 --> 00:49:06,359
发现了一样东西
...at the bottom of a ditch.

517
00:49:06,435 --> 00:49:09,667
他发现这个东西的消息传遍各地…
And the cry of his discovery was heard clear across the continent...

518
00:49:09,740 --> 00:49:12,835
波士顿…纽约…莎凡那…甚至横越大洋
...in Boston, New York, Savannah, and across the oceans...

519
00:49:11,031 --> 00:49:14,535


520
00:49:13,012 --> 00:49:14,844
至伦敦…巴黎…柏林
...in London, Paris, Berlin.

521
00:49:15,316 --> 00:49:17,979
然而这场黄金热最疯狂的地点
But nowhere was the clamor of gold...

522
00:49:18,621 --> 00:49:21,318
就是在圣路易斯市…
...heard more eagerly than in St. Louis...

523
00:49:21,659 --> 00:49:24,094
该地是全世界最忙碌的皮毛交易中心
...the busiest fur trading center in the world...

524
00:49:24,330 --> 00:49:28,325
是纽约以西最喧嚣，最态意妄为 最骄气的城市
...and the noisiest, bawdiest, most uppity town west of New York.

525
00:49:28,215 --> 00:49:30,050
（明星歌舞团）

526
00:49:30,217 --> 00:49:32,261
（登台演唱者：莉莉普莱斯考特）

527
00:49:55,479 --> 00:49:57,174
"Boys, hold your hosses

528
00:49:57,448 --> 00:49:59,075
"We're still the bosses

529
00:49:59,118 --> 00:50:00,585
"Please hold your hosses

530
00:50:00,654 --> 00:50:02,486
"Till we get...

531
00:50:02,925 --> 00:50:05,724
"...to the dance! "

532
00:50:18,181 --> 00:50:20,412
我说不超过三号
I say there's no more than three.

533
00:50:20,786 --> 00:50:23,620
- 六号 - 六号？
Six? It's all that lace that fooled you. I still say three.

534
00:50:20,809 --> 00:50:22,937
是那些蕾丝的关系 我说是三号

535
00:50:23,691 --> 00:50:26,092
克里夫可是女人衬裙专家
Watch him. I hear Cleve's an expert on petticoats.

536
00:50:26,161 --> 00:50:27,628
反正你永远没办法证实
Anyway, you can never prove it.

537
00:50:27,663 --> 00:50:29,791
咱们扑克牌局要迟到了
Gentlemen, we're going to be late for that poker game.

538
00:50:29,866 --> 00:50:32,597
我刚让你花了那么多钱 吃晚餐…
I've just stuck you for the most expensive dinner in St. Louis...

539
00:50:32,671 --> 00:50:34,731
我还想再捞你一笔 我赌一百元那件衬裙不超过六号
...and I don't mind sticking you a little bit deeper.

540
00:50:34,808 --> 00:50:36,709
我赌一百元那件衬裙不超过六号
I'll lay you $100 if it's no less than six.

541
00:50:36,777 --> 00:50:39,440
- 你要如何证实？ - 到后台去查啊
-How will you prove it? -Go backstage and find out.

542
00:50:39,515 --> 00:50:40,948
- 我和你一起去
If I go back and check with you.

543
00:50:41,018 --> 00:50:42,110
- 可以
Fair enough.

544
00:50:50,032 --> 00:50:51,124
第二个女孩
Second girl.

545
00:50:55,574 --> 00:50:57,600
- 普莱斯考特小姐？普莱斯考特小姐？ - 等一下
-Miss Prescott? -Later.

546
00:50:57,710 --> 00:50:59,268
这事挺重要的
It's rather important.

547
00:51:00,215 --> 00:51:01,807
每次都说很重要
It's always important.

548
00:51:01,884 --> 00:51:04,479
愈老的家伙事情愈重要
The older they are, the more important it gets.

549
00:51:04,554 --> 00:51:07,023
普莱斯考特小姐 我是海蓝席贝瑞…
Miss Prescott, please. I'm Hylan Seabury...

550
00:51:07,526 --> 00:51:09,995
强纳森布鲁克斯的律师
...attorney in the matter of Jonathan Brooks.

551
00:51:10,865 --> 00:51:12,595
你不知道他是谁？
He means nothing to you?

552
00:51:12,934 --> 00:51:14,231
那糟老头？
That old goat?

553
00:51:14,504 --> 00:51:16,871
那你一定对他具有某种意义 普莱斯考特小姐
You must've meant something to him, Miss Prescott.

554
00:51:16,940 --> 00:51:19,000
- 为什么？ - 他的遗嘱里有提到你
-Why? -You're included in his will.

555
00:51:19,078 --> 00:51:22,880
当然，你得亲自去加州取得这份遗产
Of course, you'll have to make the trip to California to claim the bequest.

556
00:51:22,950 --> 00:51:25,215
我才不要去加州
Well, now, I wouldn't go to California...

557
00:51:25,287 --> 00:51:28,223
就算约翰亚斯特把整个旧金山留给我
...if John Jacob Astor left me San Francisco.

558
00:51:28,693 --> 00:51:31,060
我想亚斯特先生在那里并没有财产
I don't think Mr. Astor had holdings there.

559
00:51:31,130 --> 00:51:34,727
无论如何，布鲁克斯先生物产的收入 可是不容轻忽的
However, the yield from Mr. Brooks' property is not to be scorned.

560
00:51:34,803 --> 00:51:35,963
- 什么收入？
Yield of what?

561
00:51:36,038 --> 00:51:38,064
- 黄金，普莱斯考特小姐，黄金
Gold, Miss Prescott. Gold.

562
00:51:39,142 --> 00:51:40,940
- 黄金？ - 正是
-Gold? -Precisely.

563
00:51:41,246 --> 00:51:43,112
你拥有一座金矿，普莱斯考特小姐
You own a gold mine, Miss Prescott.

564
00:51:43,183 --> 00:51:46,153
首周便收入三千五百元
It yielded $3,500 the very first week.

565
00:51:47,122 --> 00:51:48,589
金矿？
Gold mine?

567
00:51:54,233 --> 00:51:56,031
这个…我… 那个可爱的糟老头
That sweet old goat!

568
00:51:59,700 --> 00:52:01,702
老天…

569
00:52:13,213 --> 00:52:14,965
呃…

570
00:52:15,868 --> 00:52:17,666
真是意想不到的惊喜
This is an unexpected pleasure.

571
00:52:17,771 --> 00:52:18,795
- 钱呢？ - 钱？
Where's the money?

572
00:52:18,905 --> 00:52:19,872
钱？
Money?

573
00:52:20,040 --> 00:52:21,007
Money?

574
00:52:21,243 --> 00:52:25,045
喔，对了…你指的是 我们之前的小小协议
Oh, yes. You're referring, of course, to our little agreement.

575
00:52:26,049 --> 00:52:27,984
先拿出一百元吧…
One hundred to start you off...

576
00:52:28,421 --> 00:52:30,617
另外还有我赢钱的部分
...and my share of the winnings.

577
00:52:31,692 --> 00:52:35,960
真不好意思…那一百元已经没有了
Well, I'm somewhat embarrassed to report that the $100 no longer exists.

578
00:52:38,202 --> 00:52:40,171
那一百元…我可以向你保证…
That $100, I assure you...

579
00:52:40,239 --> 00:52:43,972
将是你有史以来做过最棒的投资
...will turn out to be the best investment you have ever made.

580
00:52:45,046 --> 00:52:46,776
我有几个计昼，各位
I have plans, gentlemen...

581
00:52:47,250 --> 00:52:49,185
是你们从未想过的计昼
...beyond your wildest dreams.

582
00:52:50,188 --> 00:52:53,853
我要替你们赢来一座金矿的股份
I'm gonna earn you a piece of a gold mine.

583
00:52:54,328 --> 00:52:55,352
金矿
Gold mine!

584
00:52:56,865 --> 00:52:58,697
你才不可能会赚到什么钱
You ain't gonna earn nothin'!

585
00:52:58,901 --> 00:53:01,894
你永远都不成气候 做不了任何事…
You ain't gonna be nothin', you ain't gonna do nothin'...

586
00:53:01,973 --> 00:53:03,999
除非你在明早之前 给我们一百元！
...unless we get that $100 back by the morning.

587
00:53:04,043 --> 00:53:06,035
格兰姆斯，你这话不是认真的吧
Grimes, you don't mean that.

588
00:53:06,747 --> 00:53:08,682
- 你可别干掉会下金蛋的鹅
You're gonna kill off the golden goose.

589
00:53:08,750 --> 00:53:10,480
- 随便你怎么讲，先生
Call it what you want, mister.

590
00:53:10,753 --> 00:53:12,050
我们会等着收钱的
We'll be waitin'.

591
00:53:32,751 --> 00:53:34,211
（加州一奥勒冈 篷车队）

592
00:53:35,125 --> 00:53:39,757
密苏里州的独立市是 移民者通往各地的起点
Independence, Missouri, was the jump-off point for emigrants from everywhere.

593
00:53:40,467 --> 00:53:44,098
脚踏实地，敬畏上帝 前往奥勒冈的务农人家…
Solid, God-fearing families bound for the farmlands of Oregon...

594
00:53:45,074 --> 00:53:50,013
以及前往加州淘金 梦想一夜致富的冒险者
...and get-rich-quick adventurers raced for the gold of California.

595
00:53:52,954 --> 00:53:54,012
试试看
Try it.

596
00:53:59,932 --> 00:54:01,399
- 你有篷车吧？
You got a wagon, I suppose?

597
00:54:01,501 --> 00:54:02,763
- 我可以买一辆
I can get one.

598
00:54:02,869 --> 00:54:04,131
有人帮你拉？
And a team to pull it?

599
00:54:04,171 --> 00:54:05,969
我需要的一切都有了
I can get everything I need.

600
00:54:06,308 --> 00:54:07,798
- 你有丈夫吗？
You got a husband?

601
00:54:07,843 --> 00:54:09,538
- 我单身，摩根先生
I'm single, Mr. Morgan.

602
00:54:10,114 --> 00:54:11,775
没有旅伴？
No travelin' companion?

603
00:54:12,384 --> 00:54:14,182
- 没，我一个人
No, I'm travelin' alone.

604
00:54:14,287 --> 00:54:15,914
- 我的篷车队可不行这样
Not on my wagon train.

605
00:54:16,557 --> 00:54:19,391
单身女人会引来男人妄想
Alone and single brings out the deviltry in a man.

606
00:54:19,462 --> 00:54:22,830
把他们弄得六神无主 他们已经够狂野了
Gets 'em all worked up and they're wild enough already.

607
00:54:23,001 --> 00:54:25,334
我不打算和别人打交道，摩根先生
I intend to keep to myself, Mr. Morgan.

608
00:54:26,239 --> 00:54:28,037
喔，像你这种女人？
A woman of your sort?

609
00:54:29,011 --> 00:54:33,814
有一天你会发现自己惹了麻烦 才苦恼不晓得到底要找谁算帐
One day you'd find yourself in trouble and there'd be hell to pay just figurin' out who.

610
00:54:34,051 --> 00:54:36,247
你说什么，摩根先生？
What did you say, Mr. Morgan?

611
00:54:37,490 --> 00:54:41,485
你这女人个性挺泼辣的嘛 我喜欢个性强的女人
Well, now, ain't you the feisty one! I like spirit in a woman.

612
00:54:41,737 --> 00:54:46,033


613
00:54:43,867 --> 00:54:46,428
你这张藏在妆底下的脸 还挺好看的
You got a pretty face under that powder, too.

614
00:54:46,972 --> 00:54:49,874
在这层衣服底下 应是一副美好结实的身子，我想
And a fine, sturdy body under them clothes, I wager.

615
00:54:52,981 --> 00:54:55,280
有个女人姓克雷格 艾姬克雷格
There's a woman named Clegg, Aggie Clegg.

616
00:54:56,053 --> 00:54:57,645
你去找她吧
Why don't you go see her?

617
00:55:06,069 --> 00:55:07,127
谢谢
Thanks.

618
00:55:16,886 --> 00:55:18,148
我告诉你了，不要！
I told you, no.

619
00:55:19,090 --> 00:55:21,582
我打算在这场旅途上找个丈夫
I was hoping to make this trip with a husband.

620
00:55:22,094 --> 00:55:23,926
上周差点找到一个
Nearly got one last week.

621
00:55:24,030 --> 00:55:27,159
我听说在加州每四十个男人 只有一个女人
Look, I hear there's 40 men to every woman in California.

622
00:55:27,704 --> 00:55:29,570
- 克雷格小姐，我愿意付你钱 - 我不需要钱
Miss Clegg, I'd be willing to pay you.

623
00:55:29,640 --> 00:55:32,439
我需要的是男人
I don't need money, I need a man.

624
00:55:34,948 --> 00:55:36,040
任何男人都行
Any man.

625
00:55:43,295 --> 00:55:44,557
早安，女士们
Mornin', ladies.

626
00:55:45,998 --> 00:55:47,295
今早天气真好
Beautiful mornin'.

627
00:55:48,737 --> 00:55:52,105
请问你是不是 莉莉普莱斯考特小姐？
Would you, by any chance, happen to be Miss Lily Prescott?

628
00:55:52,743 --> 00:55:55,042
除非你脑子搞不清楚
Not unless you got a big imagination.

629
00:55:55,113 --> 00:55:57,446
那一定就是你罗
Then, you must be the lady in question.

630
00:55:58,151 --> 00:56:00,586
克里夫凡伟伦，普莱斯考特小姐 听从你吩咐
Cleve van Valen, Miss Prescott, at your service.

631
00:56:00,655 --> 00:56:03,352
从这里到加州 敝人听从你差遣
At your every command from here to California.

632
00:56:03,526 --> 00:56:06,986
谢谢你
Well, thank you, but whatever you're offering, I don't need.

633
00:56:04,736 --> 00:56:08,073
不过，你提供的任何服务 我都不需要

634
00:56:08,501 --> 00:56:10,402
或许你不了解…
Perhaps you don't understand.

635
00:56:10,504 --> 00:56:13,998
是的，我了解 对于识别骗子我特别在行
Yes, I do. I know a tinhorn when I see one.

636
00:56:14,477 --> 00:56:15,671
普莱斯考特小姐…
Miss Prescott!

637
00:56:16,045 --> 00:56:19,174
我是真心想替你做事 做一份事，拿一分钱
I'm offerin' you an honest days' work for an honest days' pay.

638
00:56:19,251 --> 00:56:21,618
再见，凡伟伦先生 再见
Goodbye, Mr. van Valen. Goodbye.

639
00:56:23,792 --> 00:56:26,591
很荣幸认识你，克雷格小姐
Well, it's been a pleasure to meet you, Miss Clegg.

640
00:56:26,663 --> 00:56:31,068
请容我说，我从未过过女人 拥有一头如此美丽的秀发
May I say I have never seen a woman with more beautiful hair.

641
00:56:32,071 --> 00:56:34,165
我想那头发如果挂在…
What a prize catch it will make...

642
00:56:34,575 --> 00:56:37,044
印地安人腰上一定很好看
...hanging from the waist of an Indian.

643
00:56:37,780 --> 00:56:40,011
如此美女独自在荒野里
Beauty, alone in the wilderness...

644
00:56:40,250 --> 00:56:42,151
谁来保护你呢？
...and who's to protect you?

645
00:56:42,621 --> 00:56:43,781
没人
No one.

646
00:56:44,057 --> 00:56:47,722
每个人都自顾不暇了
Not one person won't be looking after himself.

647
00:56:51,035 --> 00:56:52,024
好吧…
Well....

648
00:56:54,440 --> 00:56:55,737
日安，女士们
Good day, ladies.

649
00:56:56,310 --> 00:56:57,368
…日安
Good day.

650
00:57:02,085 --> 00:57:04,452
从来都没有人那样对我说过
Nobody ever said that to me before.

651
00:57:05,424 --> 00:57:06,413
说什么？
What?

652
00:57:07,527 --> 00:57:10,292
说我有一头美丽的秀发
That I had such...such beautiful hair.

653
00:57:14,271 --> 00:57:15,761
你知道吗？
You know something?

654
00:57:16,609 --> 00:57:20,206
我感觉你可以吸引来许多男人
I got a hunch you're gonna draw men like fish to the bait.

655
00:57:21,349 --> 00:57:24,251
或许我可以顺便挑中一个
Maybe I can catch one of them while they swim by.

656
00:57:25,890 --> 00:57:27,722
我愿意当你的伙伴
You got yourself a partner.

657
00:57:28,627 --> 00:57:29,651
谢谢你
Thank you.

658
00:57:31,865 --> 00:57:33,230
怎么样？
How's it, Ben?

659
00:57:34,103 --> 00:57:37,768
从这里一切净空 下一段路小心一个小泥坑就是了
It's all clear up through here. Look for a little mudhole up through the next pocket.

660
00:57:37,808 --> 00:57:39,800
- 有多远？ - 喔，大约八分之一哩路吧
-How far? -Maybe half or a quarter.

661
00:57:39,878 --> 00:57:43,178
- 好的，谢谢 - 在那山脊上可登高望远
-Well, thanks. -Looks a little higher up on that ridge.

662
00:57:43,350 --> 00:57:47,118
上面有个水洞 差不多半哩，咱们往那里去
There's a water hole up there about half a mile. Let's head for it.

663
00:57:54,567 --> 00:57:56,763
前面半哩处有个水洞
Water hole about a half a mile ahead.

664
00:58:01,345 --> 00:58:02,744
嘿，你在拉车
Hey, you're drivin'.

665
00:58:04,150 --> 00:58:05,811
我是在农场里长大的
I was raised on a farm.

666
00:58:10,193 --> 00:58:12,526
前面半哩处有个水洞
Water hole about a half a mile ahead.

667
00:58:50,323 --> 00:58:51,517
嘿，艾姬？
Hey, Aggie....

668
00:58:52,926 --> 00:58:54,359
- 这个你要吗？ - 当然
Can you use these?

669
00:58:54,429 --> 00:58:56,694
谢谢
Yeah, sure. Thanks.

670
00:59:10,722 --> 00:59:11,746
女士们
Ladies.

671
00:59:21,672 --> 00:59:23,264
听从你吩咐
At your service.

672
00:59:23,642 --> 00:59:25,303
我以为已经把你给甩了
I thought we'd gotten rid of you.

673
00:59:25,378 --> 00:59:29,441
我无法想像你们俩独自上路 没有我从旁相助
Well, I just couldn't bear to think of you two makin' this trip without my help.

674
00:59:29,484 --> 00:59:31,817
我若听到你有个三长两短
If I was to hear later on that somethin' happened to you...

675
00:59:31,888 --> 00:59:33,446
我一定不会原谅我自己的
...l'd never forgive myself.

676
00:59:33,491 --> 00:59:35,049
你一个人跑一百哩？
You came 100 miles alone?

677
00:59:35,327 --> 00:59:39,663
我没计算路程，摩根先生 不过你说了就算
Well, I had no way of countin' the miles, Mr. Morgan, but I'll take your word for it.

678
00:59:39,700 --> 00:59:41,965
那你得再跑个一百哩，先生 往回走
You've got another 100, mister. Goin' back.

679
00:59:42,004 --> 00:59:45,441
我说过，当篷车坏掉时 我要懂得修车的人…
I told ya, when a wagon breaks down, I want men who can fix it...

680
00:59:45,510 --> 00:59:46,738
不是赌车子能撑多久的人
...not bet how long it'll take.

681
00:59:46,811 --> 00:59:48,803
你不会想就这样把我赶跑吧？
You don't mean you'll turn me out?

682
00:59:49,116 --> 00:59:51,813
让我沦落入野蛮印地安人手中？
Pass me adrift at the mercy of savage Indians?

683
00:59:51,853 --> 00:59:54,084
如果你再不走 我就把你…
If you don't get movin', I'll cast you adrift--

684
00:59:54,324 --> 00:59:56,623
我知道你想要讲什么，先生
I appeal to your sportin' instinct, sir.

685
00:59:57,362 --> 01:00:00,491
我要和你打赌 我将留在这车队里
I'm prepared to wager you that I stay with this train.

686
01:00:00,566 --> 01:00:01,533
- 你要赌，来啊！
Well, you got a wager.

687
01:00:01,602 --> 01:00:03,332
- 等一下！等一下！
Wait a minute.

688
01:00:03,738 --> 01:00:05,707
是这样的，我雇请了这个人
The fact is, I hired this man.

689
01:00:06,042 --> 01:00:08,011
我们愿意替他作保
We'll put up his stake.

690
01:00:10,582 --> 01:00:12,414
是这样吗，普莱斯考特小姐？
Is that right, Miss Prescott?

691
01:00:12,485 --> 01:00:14,043
克雷格小姐说了算数
If Miss Clegg says so.

692
01:00:25,773 --> 01:00:26,831
小姐…
Ma'am...

693
01:00:27,943 --> 01:00:29,775
我将毕生感激不尽
...l'll be forever grateful.

694
01:00:33,552 --> 01:00:35,612
我这就去卸下我的行李
Now, I'll unpack my gear.

695
01:00:39,795 --> 01:00:41,991
艾姬莎，你疯啦？
Agatha, have you gone crazy?

696
01:00:42,700 --> 01:00:45,636
他说他想老老实实做事
He says he's a man wantin' to do an honest days work.

697
01:00:46,773 --> 01:00:49,470
他可以的，我跟你保证
And he'll do it. I can promise you that.

698
01:00:50,812 --> 01:00:53,941
最后一台篷车 快点跟上
Hey, you men on that last wagon, keep up that slack.

699
01:00:54,017 --> 01:00:55,109
快点跟上
Keep it up.

700
01:00:56,222 --> 01:00:58,748
大家往前走，继续往前走！
Get that team movin'. Keep 'em movin' there.

701
01:01:02,231 --> 01:01:04,496
别让绳索垂下去！
Don't let those lines sag.

702
01:01:06,170 --> 01:01:07,831
跟上队伍！跟上队伍！
Keep 'em up. Keep 'em up.

703
01:01:12,480 --> 01:01:13,913
大家继续往前进！
Keep those teams movin'.

704
01:01:16,753 --> 01:01:18,015
继续往前进！
Keep 'em movin'.

705
01:01:19,524 --> 01:01:21,116
别让绳索垂下去！
Don't let those lines sag.

706
01:01:22,696 --> 01:01:24,688
队伍中间的人 继续往前进！
You on that middle team, keep 'em movin'.

707
01:01:35,549 --> 01:01:37,541
- 进去！ - 在这里，爸
Get in there.

708
01:01:37,110 --> 01:01:38,904
进去！

709
01:01:40,157 --> 01:01:42,524
进去！进去！骡子！
Get in there, mule.

710
01:02:17,315 --> 01:02:20,717
我受到如此多关心真的很感动 普莱斯考特小姐
I'm just overwhelmed by all this attention, Miss Prescott.

711
01:02:29,201 --> 01:02:30,759
我要向你坦白…
I want to confess...

712
01:02:31,372 --> 01:02:34,969
关于替你工作的事 我对你们撒谎
...I have lied about why I wanted to work for you.

713
01:02:36,580 --> 01:02:37,638
我知道
I know.

714
01:02:39,117 --> 01:02:42,246
真正的原因是 我爱上了你
The real reason is, of course, that I'm in love with you.

715
01:02:42,956 --> 01:02:45,050
先别说话…， 那是实话
Now, it's the truth.

717
01:02:45,927 --> 01:02:47,987
打从我第一眼看到你
From the first moment I saw you...

718
01:02:48,297 --> 01:02:50,960
我就知道我不能没有你
...l've known that I couldn't live without you.

719
01:02:53,372 --> 01:02:56,604
我可不想害你活不成，凡伟伦先生
I'd hate to be the cause of your death, Mr. van Valen.

720
01:02:57,780 --> 01:02:59,942
我这话可不是随便说说 普莱斯考特小姐
I don't speak lightly, Miss Prescott.

721
01:02:59,983 --> 01:03:03,648
我已准备好当个负责任且忠实的好丈夫
I'm prepared to assume the responsibilities of a faithful husband.

722
01:03:04,424 --> 01:03:07,918
喔，那你是否已准备承担责任…
Oh, and are you ready to assume the responsibilities...

723
01:03:07,996 --> 01:03:10,261
掌管我的财产呢，凡伟伦先生？
...of my property, too, Mr. van Valen?

724
01:03:11,435 --> 01:03:14,964
真的？什么样的财产？
Really? What, what kind of property?

726
01:03:16,242 --> 01:03:17,869
黄金，凡伟伦先生
Gold, Mr. van Valen.

727
01:03:18,312 --> 01:03:21,009
就我所知，有上吨的黄金
Gold by the ton from what I understand.

728
01:03:21,751 --> 01:03:24,152
闪亮，澄黄，耀眼的黄金
Bright, yellow, shiny gold.


730
01:03:28,328 --> 01:03:30,058
哇！我不晓得呢
I had no idea.

731
01:03:31,900 --> 01:03:33,128
- 我想也是
I'm sure you hadn't.

732
01:03:33,202 --> 01:03:35,137
- 普莱斯考特小姐，我真的是…
Miss Prescott, I really mean--

733
01:03:35,673 --> 01:03:37,038
艾姬莎来了
Here comes Agatha.

734
01:03:37,809 --> 01:03:39,903
如果你必须向人求婚…
If you must propose to somebody...

735
01:03:40,213 --> 01:03:42,842
我建议你向她下跪求婚
...I suggest you get on your knees to her.

736
01:03:43,051 --> 01:03:45,213
更何况，她有一头美丽的秀发
Besides, she has beautiful hair.

737
01:03:48,059 --> 01:03:49,185
瞧瞧他们…
Look at 'em.

738
01:03:49,928 --> 01:03:52,864
他们好像准备要埋葬死人一样
You'd think they was gettin' ready to bury somebody.

739
01:03:52,967 --> 01:03:55,061
难道咱们还不够苦闷吗？
Ain't we worn down enough as it is?

740
01:03:56,072 --> 01:03:58,303
那咱们来激发点士气
Well, let's wake 'em up.

741
01:04:02,849 --> 01:04:04,248
听着，各位…
Listen, everybody.

742
01:04:05,253 --> 01:04:08,884
来吧，每个人都来
"Come on along, everybody come along

743
01:04:09,459 --> 01:04:12,429
这里有明亮的月亮和星光
"While that moon am shinin' bright

744
01:04:13,299 --> 01:04:16,896
来吧，放开你的嗓门一起歌唱
"Come on along And raise your voice in song

745
01:04:16,938 --> 01:04:20,272
今天晚我们要骚动起来
"We're gonna raise a ruckus tonight

746
01:04:21,378 --> 01:04:25,009
我们没时间坐着，一起骚动起来
"It ain't no time to sit 'n brood Raise a ruckus tonight

747
01:04:25,284 --> 01:04:29,188
调动你的热情一起骚动起来
"It's time to strike a lively mood Raise a ruckus tonight

748
01:04:29,424 --> 01:04:33,260
雷兹，去把你的班卓琴弹起来让大家热情骚动起来
"Go and get that old banjo Raise a ruckus tonight

749
01:04:33,430 --> 01:04:37,061
只需要拍着节奏让你的脚和身体骚动起来
"Just pat your foot and tap your toe Raise a ruckus tonight

750
01:04:37,136 --> 01:04:41,438
你听到了我说的吗？来吧，孩子们，来吧
"Do ya hear me? Come on along, little children, come along

751
01:04:42,144 --> 01:04:44,841
这里有明亮的月亮和星光
"While that moon am shinin' bright

752
01:04:44,982 --> 01:04:49,011
过来，把这把洗衣板当琴弦弹
"Come along now and tune up that string And let that banjo ring

753
01:04:49,121 --> 01:04:52,581
今天晚我们要骚动起来
"We're gonna raise a ruckus tonight! "

754
01:04:53,228 --> 01:04:54,855
现在唱出来吧！
Sing it out, now!

755
01:05:23,509 --> 01:05:26,502
这样才对嘛！士气激昂！
That's the spirit. That's the way to feel.

756
01:05:35,662 --> 01:05:37,289
喔，你好哇，摩根先生！
Oh, hiya, Mr. Morgan!

757
01:05:51,286 --> 01:05:53,278
艾姬…午餐吃的
Aggie, for lunch.

758
01:05:54,058 --> 01:05:56,186
谢谢，好一篓肥鱼
Thanks. Nice not to fish.

759
01:06:04,908 --> 01:06:06,398
什么事，摩根先生？
What is it, Mr. Morgan?

760
01:06:07,278 --> 01:06:09,975
普莱斯考特小姐，我一直在想…
Miss Prescott, I've been thinking.

761
01:06:15,091 --> 01:06:17,993
你是我走遍各地 见过最美丽的女人
Wet or dry, you're the handsomest woman I ever did see.

762
01:06:18,463 --> 01:06:20,329
个性活泼，身材健美
Spirit and a fine sturdy body.

763
01:06:21,468 --> 01:06:23,960
绝佳组合，普莱斯考特小姐
It's a noble combination, Miss Prescott.

764
01:06:24,271 --> 01:06:28,141
我想生孩子对你而言应该就像 滚木头一样简单
Why, for you, child-bearin' would come as easy as rolling off a log.

765
01:06:30,415 --> 01:06:34,012
我还宁愿滚木头呢，摩根先生
Well, I think I'd rather roll off a log, Mr. Morgan.

766
01:06:35,022 --> 01:06:37,651
小姐，我告诉你 你绝对是生孩子的料
Ma'am, I'm tellin' you, you got the build for it.

767
01:06:38,227 --> 01:06:39,717
我要你当我的老婆
I want you for my wife.

768
01:06:41,065 --> 01:06:43,591
我在麻塞德有一座牧牛农场
I've got a cattle ranch just below the Merced.

769
01:06:44,337 --> 01:06:46,966
我将在那里安顿下来 衣食无缺
I'll be settlin' down there, fit and proper.

770
01:06:48,476 --> 01:06:51,173
我相信你是很衣食无缺 摩根先生
I'm sure you're very fit and proper, Mr. Morgan.

771
01:06:52,115 --> 01:06:53,241
那么…
Well, then...

772
01:06:53,684 --> 01:06:56,620
你不可能嫁给比我更好的人
...you just couldn't do no better than marryin' me.

773
01:06:57,123 --> 01:07:00,218
我们可以很快地组个美满家庭 生儿育女
Why, we'd have ourselves a fine family in no time at all.

774
01:07:02,131 --> 01:07:03,325
我相信是可以的
I believe that.

775
01:07:05,270 --> 01:07:07,330
我很抱歉，摩根先生…
I'm sorry, Mr. Morgan, but...

776
01:07:08,341 --> 01:07:09,774
我无法接受你的求婚
...I can't accept your proposal.

777
01:07:10,011 --> 01:07:11,069
为什么不？
Why not?

778
01:07:12,381 --> 01:07:13,370
Well....

779
01:07:13,583 --> 01:07:16,678
女人喜欢听点甜言蜜语的话
A woman likes to hear something a little more inviting.

780
01:07:18,056 --> 01:07:21,049
那不就是我的意思？ 对你甜言蜜语
Well, ain't that what I've been doin'? Invitin' you?

781
01:07:21,595 --> 01:07:24,224
请你和我分享我的人生 普莱斯考特小姐
Invitin' you to share my life, Miss Prescott.

782
01:07:27,305 --> 01:07:28,772
很抱歉，摩根先生…
I'm sorry, Mr. Morgan.

783
01:07:31,277 --> 01:07:33,246
是不是有别的事情？
It's somethin' else, ain't it?

784
01:07:34,416 --> 01:07:36,647
一定有别的事情困扰着你
Must be somethin' else naggin' at you.

786
01:07:40,258 --> 01:07:42,727
好吧… 我不会让它阻止我的 普莱斯考特小姐
I don't aim to let it stop me, Miss Prescott.

787
01:07:44,365 --> 01:07:45,855
我向你保证
You can count on that.

788
01:07:46,301 --> 01:07:47,598
他想要什么？
What did he want?

789
01:07:49,473 --> 01:07:50,565
孩子
Children.

790
01:07:51,776 --> 01:07:52,834
孩子？
Children?

791
01:07:53,512 --> 01:07:54,706
真是的…
Well, I'll be--

792
01:07:56,149 --> 01:07:58,744
他干嘛不找对的人呢？
Why didn't he come shopping at the right store?

793
01:08:42,356 --> 01:08:43,653
- 我押这些 - 这个嘛…
I'll take a look.

794
01:08:45,561 --> 01:08:47,325
咱们是玩小赌本吗？
Gentlemen, are we pikers?

795
01:08:47,431 --> 01:08:50,595
我要再加筹码 还要再押这把好枪…
I'm gonna see and I'm gonna raise this fine pistol.

796
01:08:50,703 --> 01:08:53,298
伦敦制，专门打熊用的枪
London-made and loaded for bear.

797
01:08:53,841 --> 01:08:55,673
我也要参加一份
I'll take part of that bet.

798
01:09:03,222 --> 01:09:05,987
我说过我绝不允许你搞这种勾当…
I told you I wouldn't stand for you fleecin' any--

799
01:09:09,265 --> 01:09:10,357
夏安族
Cheyennes.

800
01:09:11,569 --> 01:09:13,970
我们寡不敌众 必须赶紧逃跑
There's too many. We'll have to make a run for it.

801
01:09:14,207 --> 01:09:15,469
用篷车根本跑不过他们
You can't outrun them with the wagons.

802
01:09:15,541 --> 01:09:17,806
一开跑之后 整个队伍要散开
The minute you get movin' cut your lead teams loose.

803
01:09:17,879 --> 01:09:19,210
- 你疯啦？ - 快点，动作快！
Have you gone crazy?

804
01:09:20,349 --> 01:09:22,215
他们要的是我们的货 不是我们的人
Chances are they want our stock more than us.

805
01:09:22,252 --> 01:09:24,380
你是赌徒没错吧？ 好了，咱们走吧
You're a gambler, ain't you? All right, let's get movin'.

806
01:09:42,384 --> 01:09:43,942
大家凑紧一点！
Keep 'em closed up there.

807
01:09:55,939 --> 01:09:57,703
我不知道该如何解开它们
I don't know how to unhook them.

808
01:11:02,377 --> 01:11:04,072
克里夫，小心！
Cleve, watch out!


810
01:12:06,544 --> 01:12:08,171
乔！载我一程！
Joe, pick me up.

811
01:12:54,754 --> 01:12:56,723
天一破晓我们就出发
We'll be movin' at daybreak.

812
01:12:57,158 --> 01:12:59,992
我带几个人去看能不能找到他
I'll take a few men and see if we can find him.

813
01:13:00,162 --> 01:13:02,688
帮他好好做一场基督徒的葬礼仪式
Give him a decent, Christian burial.

814
01:13:10,579 --> 01:13:12,741
有人来了！有人来了！
Someone's comin'! Someone's comin'!

815
01:13:57,687 --> 01:14:01,455
这车子我可以租你一天一块钱 还可以派人手随同
I can let you have this rig for $1 a day and I'll give you a good team.

816
01:14:01,693 --> 01:14:03,457
- 明天早上来取 - 好的
-Pick it up in the morning. -Fine.

817
01:14:03,696 --> 01:14:05,995
请问布鲁克斯家往哪里走？
Could you tell me the way to the Brook's claim?

818
01:14:06,033 --> 01:14:08,366
就在河边
Well, the claims are down by the river.

819
01:14:08,904 --> 01:14:10,166
- 我该走哪条路？
Which road should I take?

820
01:14:10,207 --> 01:14:12,301
- 只有一条路，沿着河走
Only one road, along the river.

821
01:14:12,710 --> 01:14:14,302
- 谢谢 - 不客气
-Thank you. -Sure welcome.

822
01:14:28,836 --> 01:14:30,828
我们要找赫金斯先生
We're looking for a Mr. Huggins.

823
01:14:31,240 --> 01:14:32,434
我就是
You found him.

824
01:14:37,750 --> 01:14:40,117
这位是莉莉丝普莱斯考特
This is Miss Lilith Prescott.

825
01:14:40,755 --> 01:14:41,744
我想也是
I figured.

826
01:14:42,090 --> 01:14:44,218
他们说你是个美人
They told me you was a real looker.

827
01:14:45,262 --> 01:14:48,722
这片地都是你的了 正如布鲁克斯声明的
It's all here for you. Just the way Mr. Brooks staked it out.

828
01:14:48,967 --> 01:14:50,799
从前大概有二十人在工作
Must have had 20 men workin' on it.

829
01:14:51,405 --> 01:14:54,000
那现在人呢？ 是谁在挖黄金呢？
Where are they now? Who's digging the gold?

830
01:14:54,109 --> 01:14:58,047
黄金？我和米莉来这里之前 从未见过如此上等货
Gold? I ain't never seen a better grade since I come here with Millie.

831
01:14:58,983 --> 01:15:00,884
只有一点点
But just a pocket, though.

832
01:15:01,020 --> 01:15:03,489
整个庞大工程却只挖到一点点
The whole shebang, nothin' but a pocket.

833
01:15:04,292 --> 01:15:06,887
喔，我们总共赚了四千二百元
Oh, we cleared $4,200 before it played out.

834
01:15:08,164 --> 01:15:09,928
关于那四千二百元…
Now, about that $4,200....

835
01:15:10,468 --> 01:15:13,267
布鲁克斯先生在心脏病发作之前 化掉了三千元
Mr. Brooks, he spent three before his heart give out.

836
01:15:13,339 --> 01:15:15,865
我花了六百元买一座铜棺材
