1008
01:33:41,872 --> 01:33:43,862
喔，有好多事要做
Well, there'll be things to do.

1009
01:33:46,145 --> 01:33:47,133
妈…
Ma....

1010
01:33:49,749 --> 01:33:53,081
我得帮你洗内裤 补袜子的破洞
I've gotta get your underwear washed and your socks darned.

1011
01:33:56,390 --> 01:33:58,687
他们会给你那种衣服吗？
Do they give you one of them suits?

1012
01:33:59,697 --> 01:34:01,220
那种制服？
One of them uniforms?

1013
01:34:02,867 --> 01:34:03,855
会的
I reckon.

1014
01:34:06,203 --> 01:34:08,762
可能不会给你衬衣
They might not give you no shirts though.

1015
01:34:09,108 --> 01:34:11,507
把那件脱下来 我帮你洗
Take that one off. I'll wash it for you.

1016
01:34:12,380 --> 01:34:15,246
我已经洗了其他几件 还没烫过呢
I got the others washed but they aren't ironed yet.

1017
01:34:16,850 --> 01:34:17,975
母亲，我…
Mother, I....

1018
01:34:21,724 --> 01:34:23,213
你为什么那样叫我？
Why'd you call me that?

1019
01:34:23,859 --> 01:34:25,723
你总是喊我“妈”
It's always been Ma before.

1020
01:34:28,933 --> 01:34:30,058
不晓得…
I don't know.

1021
01:34:31,136 --> 01:34:32,432
突然间…
All of a sudden...

1022
01:34:33,806 --> 01:34:36,069
喊“妈”似乎已经不够了
...Ma didn't seem enough somehow.

1023
01:34:54,400 --> 01:34:57,095
嘿！小子！
Yahoo. Hey, cowpoke!

1024
01:35:51,072 --> 01:35:52,333
回去！狗狗！
Go on back, dog.

1025
01:35:54,176 --> 01:35:55,142
回去！
Go on!

1026
01:36:18,875 --> 01:36:20,239
我能怎么办，爸？
What could I do, Pa?

1027
01:36:21,411 --> 01:36:22,877
他是奈勒斯的儿子
He's Linus' boy.

1028
01:36:26,251 --> 01:36:28,241
从小到大就像奈勒斯
Always was more Linus' blood.

1029
01:36:32,292 --> 01:36:34,555
所以我才会那么爱他吧
I guess that's why I love him so much.

1030
01:36:40,569 --> 01:36:42,900
但您得帮我祈祷，爸…
But you've got to help me pray, Pa.

1031
01:36:48,180 --> 01:36:49,339
帮我祈祷
Help me pray.

1032
01:37:28,161 --> 01:37:29,127
俄亥俄！
Ohio.

1033
01:37:29,333 --> 01:37:31,266
俄亥俄州炮兵连队！
Battery "B", Ohio.

1034
01:37:32,435 --> 01:37:34,368
- 走吧！ - 快点！
-Let's go! -On the double. Come on.

1035
01:37:34,470 --> 01:37:37,768
有谁是密西根州的第十二连队？
Anybody here from the Twelfth Michigan?

1036
01:37:38,975 --> 01:37:41,135
印地安那州的三十六连队
Thirty-sixth Indiana.

1037
01:37:44,985 --> 01:37:48,078
1862年4月6日夜里…
Evening of April Sixth, 1862.

1038
01:37:49,121 --> 01:37:52,112
响彻云霄一整天的枪炮 现在恢复宁静…
The guns that had roared all day fell silent...

1039
01:37:52,394 --> 01:37:56,762
就在一间叫做沙罗会议厅 的小教堂旁边的
...around a little church called the Shiloh Meeting House.

1040
01:37:58,201 --> 01:38:00,998
许多人在那星期日都见到了上帝…
Many a man had met his God that Sunday...

1041
01:38:02,274 --> 01:38:03,672
只是不是在教堂里
...but not in church.

1042
01:38:12,320 --> 01:38:14,287
你等于在浪费时间 他已经死了
You wasted your time, men. He's dead.

1043
01:38:14,355 --> 01:38:16,345
- 不，医生，他是罗林上校
But, Doc, this here is Captain Rawlings!

1044
01:38:16,457 --> 01:38:18,515
- 奈勒斯罗林上校
Captain Linus Rawlings.

1045
01:38:18,761 --> 01:38:20,728
- 把他带出去 - 走吧
-Take him out. -Keep movin', men.

1046
01:38:30,274 --> 01:38:32,332
- 你走路干嘛不长眼睛？
Why can't you look where you're goin'?

1047
01:38:32,413 --> 01:38:33,777
- 对不起，士兵
I'm sorry, soldier.

1048
01:38:34,148 --> 01:38:35,307
小心点！
Watch it.

1049
01:38:42,591 --> 01:38:44,319
铁锯…白兰地…
Saw. Brandy.

1050
01:38:45,094 --> 01:38:46,185
麻醉剂
Chloroform.

1051
01:38:47,464 --> 01:38:48,657
全部都拿来
Get it all down.

1052
01:38:48,732 --> 01:38:50,255
全拿来！
Come on, all of it!

1053
01:38:52,435 --> 01:38:54,595
走吧，我们在这里只会碍事
Come on. We're just in the way here.

1054
01:38:59,446 --> 01:39:03,472
那是西区战事前线最血腥的一天
It had been the bloodiest day of the war on the Western front.

1055
01:39:04,620 --> 01:39:08,077
白天看起来好像邦联大获全胜
In the morning, it had looked like a Confederate victory...

1056
01:39:08,491 --> 01:39:10,117
但是一到晚上…
...but by nightfall...

1057
01:39:10,460 --> 01:39:13,895
再也没有人提到 “赢”或“输”这几个字眼
...no man cared to use the words "win" or "lose".

1058
01:39:16,868 --> 01:39:18,357
在沙罗会议厅之后…
After Shiloh...

1059
01:39:20,138 --> 01:39:21,729
南方军从未展开笑颜
...the South never smiled.

1060
01:39:36,929 --> 01:39:38,555
- 你有没有尝过这个水？ - 没有
You tasted that water yet?

1061
01:39:38,630 --> 01:39:39,926
尝尝看
-No. -Well, try it.

1062
01:39:45,837 --> 01:39:47,599
- 味道怪怪的，是吧？ - 是啊
-Tastes funny, huh? -Yeah.

1063
01:39:48,275 --> 01:39:50,538
太阳下山之前 水是粉红色的
I seen it before sundown. It was pink.

1064
01:39:51,146 --> 01:39:52,635
比黄樟茶还要红
Pinker than sassafras tea.

1065
01:39:53,782 --> 01:39:54,748
你是说…？
You mean...?

1066
01:39:54,849 --> 01:39:57,840
头脑正常的人不应该会喝这种水
It don't seem fittin' a man should have to drink water like that.

1067
01:39:57,921 --> 01:40:01,617
头脑正常的人不应该会做出 咱们今天做过的事
Don't seem fittin' a man should have to do any of the things we've done today.

1068
01:40:01,692 --> 01:40:03,420
你有没有杀人？
Did you kill anybody?

1069
01:40:04,863 --> 01:40:06,329
应该没有
I don't think so.

1070
01:40:07,434 --> 01:40:09,367
我一开始就被人打昏
I got knocked dizzy right off.

1071
01:40:10,871 --> 01:40:14,306
当我醒来之后找到我的枪 已经被弄坏了
Then when I come to and found my rifle, it was busted.

1072
01:40:16,476 --> 01:40:20,172
然后来了几个士兵拿东西刺我的手
Then some more soldiers come along and tried to stick me in the arm.

1073
01:40:22,885 --> 01:40:25,375
剩下来的部分都全混在一起了
All the rest is, is mixed up after that.

1074
01:40:25,923 --> 01:40:28,891
我也没杀任何人 我不想杀人
I ain't killed nobody, neither. And I don't want to.

1075
01:40:31,229 --> 01:40:33,321
- 你打哪来的？ - 俄亥俄州
-Hey, where you from? -Ohio.

1076
01:40:34,735 --> 01:40:38,534
这场蠢战争从东部开打 咱们西部的人干嘛淌这混水？
This fool war started in the East. What's us Westerners doin' in it?

1077
01:40:38,838 --> 01:40:40,737
我再也搞不清楚了！
I don't rightly know any more!

1078
01:40:46,216 --> 01:40:48,012
和我原来想的不太一样
It ain't quite what I expected.

1079
01:40:50,489 --> 01:40:54,254
一个开膛破肚的人 哪有任何光荣可言
There ain't much glory in lookin' at a man with his guts hangin' out.

1080
01:40:57,996 --> 01:40:59,963
- 你打哪来的？ - 德州
-Where you from? -Texas.

1081
01:41:02,437 --> 01:41:03,425
我说啊…
Say....

1082
01:41:04,406 --> 01:41:05,963
你该不会是南方军的人吧？
You ain't a Reb, are you?

1083
01:41:06,541 --> 01:41:09,907
今天早上我是的 今晚我就不确定了
Well, I was this mornin'. Tonight, I ain't so sure.

1084
01:41:11,648 --> 01:41:14,514
我好像应该得对你开枪
It seems like, I oughta be shootin' you.

1085
01:41:16,388 --> 01:41:18,651
你有东西可以射杀我吗？
Well, you got anything to shoot with?

1086
01:41:21,395 --> 01:41:22,383
没有
No.

1087
01:41:23,297 --> 01:41:24,923
我只有这把刺刀
All I got's this bayonet.

1088
01:41:26,033 --> 01:41:27,431
我有一把手枪
I got a pistol.

1089
01:41:29,271 --> 01:41:31,067
我从一个阵亡军官身上拿到的
I took it off a dead officer.

1090
01:41:34,978 --> 01:41:37,411
咱们何不溜出这里？
Hey, why don't we skedaddle out of here?

1091
01:41:38,682 --> 01:41:40,842
- 你是说弃职潜逃？ - 为什么不呢？
-You mean desert? -I mean, why don't--

1092
01:41:40,918 --> 01:41:43,784
让那些想打仗的人去打吧
Just leave this here war to the folks who want it.

1093
01:41:49,664 --> 01:41:52,962
人家都说在加州没有战争
They say there ain't no war out in California.

1094
01:41:54,734 --> 01:41:57,445
把小队召集到这里

1095
01:41:59,876 --> 01:42:02,309
脱队者！快加入自己的小队！
Stragglers, join your regiment.

1096
01:42:02,378 --> 01:42:03,810
脱队者！嘿！你！
Stragglers! Hey, you!

1097
01:42:13,527 --> 01:42:16,825
我打算把卢梭小队移到这一区
I'm planning to move Rousseau's brigade into this area.

1098
01:42:17,565 --> 01:42:22,399
潜伏此地，在日出前部署完毕 你批准吗？
Hidden battery, placed well before dawn. Do you approve?

1099
01:42:22,471 --> 01:42:24,995
你所做的任何部署安排 我都批准
I'll approve any dispositions you want to make.

1100
01:42:25,611 --> 01:42:29,102
今天要不是你I卫侧翼 我们很可能全军覆没
If you hadn't held the flank today, we'd have been whipped for fair.

1101
01:42:30,415 --> 01:42:34,009
薛曼一自们坐一下 我有话要告诉你
Sherman, let's sit down a minute. There's somethin' I wanna say to you.

1102
01:42:36,423 --> 01:42:37,389
油灯
Lantern.

1103
01:42:43,899 --> 01:42:46,128
接下来可能由你独挑大梁了
You may find yourself in command here.

1104
01:42:46,371 --> 01:42:47,359
为什么？
Why?

1105
01:42:48,072 --> 01:42:51,871
我看过今天发刊的新闻报纸文章
I've seen some of the dispatches the newspaper correspondents...

1106
01:42:51,942 --> 01:42:53,499
...have filed today.

1107
01:42:54,079 --> 01:42:57,138
他们说今天早上的突袭 出乎我意料之外
They're sayin' I was taken by surprise this morning.

1108
01:42:57,484 --> 01:42:59,417
那并未出乎你意料之外
You weren't taken by surprise.

1109
01:43:00,154 --> 01:43:01,177
我有
I was.

1110
01:43:01,622 --> 01:43:02,679
不管怎样…
No matter.

1111
01:43:03,724 --> 01:43:04,985
他们说…
They're sayin'...

1112
01:43:06,626 --> 01:43:08,616
我昨晚又喝醉酒了
...I was drunk again last night.

1113
01:43:12,069 --> 01:43:13,035
你有吗？
Were you?

1114
01:43:16,106 --> 01:43:17,094
没有
No.

1115
01:43:18,511 --> 01:43:20,671
但是蜡烛两头烧根本行不通
But you can't fight front and rear.

1116
01:43:21,515 --> 01:43:23,004
明天无论打输或打赢…
Win or lose, tomorrow...

1117
01:43:24,785 --> 01:43:26,479
我都要辞职
...I intend to resign.

1118
01:43:28,055 --> 01:43:29,783
就因为报纸的那些文章？
Because of the newspapers?

1119
01:43:32,761 --> 01:43:35,786
因为大众对我缺乏信心
Because of the general lack of confidence in me.

1120
01:43:36,667 --> 01:43:39,066
喔，你以为我从未有过那种感受？
Don't you think I've ever felt like that?

1121
01:43:39,204 --> 01:43:42,070
一个月前他们骂我是 疯子，脑筋不正常
A month ago they were sayin' I was crazy. Insane.

1122
01:43:42,976 --> 01:43:46,672
现在他们夸我是大英雄 不管是疯子或英雄，我还是我
And now they're callin' me a hero. Hero or crazy, I'm the same man.

1123
01:43:47,813 --> 01:43:50,212
无论别人怎么想
It doesn't matter what the people think.

1124
01:43:50,453 --> 01:43:52,215
都是你自己想的，格兰特
It's what you think, Grant.

1125
01:43:54,589 --> 01:43:56,453
那就是格兰特？
You mean that's Grant?

1126
01:43:58,861 --> 01:44:00,054
是的
I reckon.

1127
01:44:00,265 --> 01:44:01,697
格兰特将军
General Grant.

1128
01:44:02,799 --> 01:44:06,234
这场战争将在西部取得胜利 如何取得胜利…
You know this war is gonna be won in the West and how to win it.

1129
01:44:06,472 --> 01:44:08,496
要由你的所作所为去证实
Everything you've done proves it.

1130
01:44:09,642 --> 01:44:13,702
一个人只有在做错事时 才有资格辞职
And I say that a man has the right to resign only if he's wrong.

1131
01:44:15,116 --> 01:44:16,605
做对事时便没有资格
Not if he's right.

1132
01:44:18,854 --> 01:44:22,050
我想我从来没那样想过
I guess I never thought of it that way.

1133
01:44:24,495 --> 01:44:25,859
我会好好考虑的
I'll think it over.

1134
01:44:26,264 --> 01:44:27,992
还有什么好考虑的？
What is there to think about?

1135
01:44:28,032 --> 01:44:31,694
军队有你在是比较好的 那便是一种考验
The Army's better off with you than without you. That's the test.

1136
01:44:36,043 --> 01:44:37,100
好吧
All right.

1137
01:44:38,045 --> 01:44:39,033
谢谢
Thanks.

1138
01:44:41,215 --> 01:44:43,808
日出之前有很多事要做，薛曼
There's a lot to do before morning, Sherman?

1139
01:44:44,253 --> 01:44:45,810
你在做什么？
What are you doin'?

1140
01:45:03,913 --> 01:45:05,641
你为什么逼我那么做？
Why'd you make me do that?

1141
01:45:54,306 --> 01:45:56,016
开火！

1142
01:46:05,756 --> 01:46:09,885
"When Johnny comes marching home again Hurrah, hurrah

1143
01:46:10,129 --> 01:46:14,292
"We'll give him a hearty welcome and Hurrah, hurrah

1144
01:46:14,635 --> 01:46:18,900
"The men will cheer, the boys will shout The ladies they will all turn out

1145
01:46:19,009 --> 01:46:23,206
"And we'll all feel gay When Johnny comes marching home

1146
01:46:23,345 --> 01:46:27,337
"Get ready to join the jubilee Hurrah, hurrah

1147
01:46:27,854 --> 01:46:31,983
"We'll drink up a toast, or two, or three Hurrah, hurrah

1148
01:46:32,192 --> 01:46:36,651
"The band will play and we'll sing for joy And all the ladies will kiss the boys

1149
01:46:36,729 --> 01:46:40,755
"And we'll all feel gay When Johnny comes marching home

1150
01:46:41,003 --> 01:46:43,334
"The men will cheer, the boys will shout"

1151
01:47:08,339 --> 01:47:10,466
（奈勒斯罗林 1810年至1862年）

1152
01:47:10,633 --> 01:47:13,469
（伊芙普莱斯考特罗林）

1153
01:47:36,207 --> 01:47:37,264
嘿，齐伯！
Hey, Zeb.

1154
01:48:03,310 --> 01:48:05,072
你没收到我的信？
Didn't you get my letter?

1155
01:48:06,813 --> 01:48:08,803
我四个多月前寄出的
I wrote more than four months ago.

1156
01:48:12,152 --> 01:48:13,413
在得知爸爸的消息之后…
She never was...

1157
01:48:14,323 --> 01:48:17,257
她整个人便再也不复从前
...quite the same after she got the news about Pa.

1158
01:48:21,197 --> 01:48:23,824
我觉得她并不害怕死亡，齐伯 只是…
I don't think she minded goin', Zeb, except...

1159
01:48:26,071 --> 01:48:28,061
她当时很想再见你一面
...she wanted to see you again.

1160
01:48:33,179 --> 01:48:35,169
当然，爸爸的尸骨并不在那里
'Course Pa ain't really there.

1161
01:48:38,487 --> 01:48:40,249
我还是立了一个碑
I put up a stone anyway.

1162
01:49:00,034 --> 01:49:01,618
好吧…

1163
01:49:02,317 --> 01:49:04,011
我得上路了
I'd better be on my way.

1164
01:49:05,052 --> 01:49:06,643
上路？去哪？
Way? Where?

1165
01:49:07,557 --> 01:49:09,046
我需要你，齐伯
I need you, Zeb.

1166
01:49:09,626 --> 01:49:11,650
我回来只为了一件事…
Only one thing brought me back...

1167
01:49:13,295 --> 01:49:14,659
她…
...and she's....

1168
01:49:15,433 --> 01:49:17,366
这个农场有一半是你的
Well, this farm is half yours.

1169
01:49:17,971 --> 01:49:22,270
我在想我们好不容易清出 河边的那条道路…
I'm thinkin' we'd finally clear away that patch of woods down by the river....

1170
01:49:22,642 --> 01:49:25,405
你比我还懂得处理农场的事 你并不需要我
You're twice the farmer I am. You don't need me.

1171
01:49:26,579 --> 01:49:29,103
农场是你的了 这样才公平
That farm's all yours. That's only fair.

1172
01:49:31,421 --> 01:49:33,615
这样我还是觉得不太好
I sure don't feel right about this.

1173
01:49:34,390 --> 01:49:36,016
那你打算去哪里？
What are you gonna do?

1174
01:49:36,160 --> 01:49:37,956
我还不晓得
I haven't mustered out yet.

1175
01:49:38,027 --> 01:49:40,221
我还可以转任当普通警官
I can still transfer to the regulars.

1176
01:49:40,365 --> 01:49:42,628
或许到西部当骑警
The cavalry, maybe. And go West.

1177
01:49:43,503 --> 01:49:45,231
去和印地安人对抗？
And have to fight Indians?

1178
01:49:46,706 --> 01:49:49,003
我真的很不了解你，齐伯
You sure are hard to make out, Zeb.

1179
01:49:49,411 --> 01:49:52,538
你干嘛要那么做？ 你喜欢打架吗？
Now, what do you wanna do that for? Do you like fightin'?

1180
01:49:54,615 --> 01:49:59,017
你还记得爸曾经告诉我们 他对抗大熊的故事吗？
Do you remember the story Pa used to tell us about fightin' that grizzly bear?

1181
01:49:59,122 --> 01:50:00,088
记得
Yeah.

1182
01:50:00,292 --> 01:50:03,522
我问他：“你为什么要做出那种事？”
And I asked him. I said: "Now, why'd you get in such a fix?

1183
01:50:03,595 --> 01:50:05,619
“你喜欢和大熊打架吗？”
"Do you like fightin' grizzlies?"

1184
01:50:06,264 --> 01:50:07,287
他说…
He said:

1185
01:50:08,066 --> 01:50:11,159
“那倒也不是…”
"Well, not 'specially.

1186
01:50:12,507 --> 01:50:16,067
“我只是想到外面闯 结果那只熊比我先到那里”
"I just wanted to go somewhere and the bear was there first."

1187
01:50:29,581 --> 01:50:31,208
所以我…

1188
01:50:34,235 --> 01:50:36,759
我想我也要出去闯了
I guess I just wanna go somewhere, too.

1189
01:50:41,309 --> 01:50:43,572
- 再会 - 再会，齐伯
-So long. -So long, Zeb.

1190
01:51:04,006 --> 01:51:06,803
正当北部和南部成分裂局势时…
Even while North and South were being torn apart...

1191
01:51:07,411 --> 01:51:11,073
东部和西部却慢慢统合 透过《驿马快递》…
...East and West had been drawn together by the Pony Express...

1192
01:51:11,414 --> 01:51:13,813
有史以来最危险的通邮服务
...the most daring mail route in history.

1193
01:51:14,053 --> 01:51:17,681
八十名骑士着邮包 风雨无阻，日以继夜地奔驰…
Eighty riders were in the saddle at all times, night and day, in all weather.

1194
01:51:17,722 --> 01:51:20,417
一半往东骑 一半往西骑…
Half of them riding east, half riding west...

1195
01:51:20,694 --> 01:51:23,059
来回于密苏里和沙加缅度之间
...between Missouri and Sacramento...

1196
01:51:23,197 --> 01:51:26,495
让邮件于几天内寄达 不用再花几个月时间
...carrying mail cross-country in days instead of months.

1197
01:51:27,335 --> 01:51:29,393
他们不配武器，只为轻便成行
Unarmed, they rode to save weight.

1198
01:51:30,272 --> 01:51:33,638
一封信邮费五元 只能寄薄薄的信纸
Five dollars a letter, the mail cost, and on thin paper, too.

1199
01:51:34,175 --> 01:51:37,041
这项服务代表着勇气 技术以及速度…
It was courage, skill and speed...

1200
01:51:37,349 --> 01:51:41,580
对抗充满敌意的印地安人，土匪 有时还得应付洪水
...against hostile Indians, bandits, hell and occasional high water.

1201
01:51:43,322 --> 01:51:46,586
在他们奔驰的同时 人们另外开始搭建…
Even as they rode, men were already building a faster...

1202
01:51:46,727 --> 01:51:50,321
更快速的横贯全国的 《大陆电报线路》
...message carrier across the country, the Overland Telegraph.

1203
01:51:50,799 --> 01:51:53,358
结果让印地安人找到新的娱乐
And the Indians found a new amusement...

1204
01:51:53,535 --> 01:51:56,469
聆听电线传送出的歌唱声音
...listening to the level tune of the singing wires.

1205
01:51:56,807 --> 01:51:59,070
可是印地安人却对另一件事 感到不快…
But far less amusing to the Indians...

1206
01:51:59,142 --> 01:52:02,372
即有铁马之称的火车铁路的到来
...was the coming of the steel roadway of the Iron Horse.

1207
01:52:03,315 --> 01:52:08,308
铁道路线预定经过 伟大的天然屏障：洛矶山脉…
The surveyors' route lay through immense natural barriers, the Rocky Mountains...

1208
01:52:09,422 --> 01:52:11,889
以及同样令人生畏的喜耶亚山区
...and the equally discouraging High Sierras.

1209
01:52:12,760 --> 01:52:16,593
然而浩瀚的崇山峻岭并无法阻挡 两家大企业…
But range upon range could never stop the titanic contest...

1210
01:52:16,696 --> 01:52:19,425
争先建造有史以来…
...between two corporate giants racing to put down...

1211
01:52:19,470 --> 01:52:22,336
最长的铁道 最后将交会会合
...the greatest mileage of track before they met:

1212
01:52:23,139 --> 01:52:26,767
《中太平洋公司》负责从沙加缅度 往东至喜耶亚山区
The Central Pacific eastward from Sacramento through the Sierras.

1213
01:52:31,652 --> 01:52:35,519
《联合太平洋公司》则横跨整个 西向平原区…
And the Union Pacific, forging westward across the plains...

1214
01:52:35,822 --> 01:52:37,812
但仍需克服洛矶山脉的屏障
...with the Rockies still to come.

1215
01:52:37,927 --> 01:52:42,795
这场竞赛的奖赏是免费土地 铁道所到之处便可获得当地广大土地
The prize in the race was free land, vast parcels for every mile of track laid.

1216
01:52:43,666 --> 01:52:46,259
将来有天，那些土地将价值百万
Land that would one day be worth millions.

1217
01:52:52,245 --> 01:52:53,268
停止
Hold it!

1218
01:52:54,313 --> 01:52:55,472
放下！
Set it down!

1219
01:52:56,615 --> 01:52:57,808
工人们，站起来！
Up!

1220
01:53:04,726 --> 01:53:06,283
你在哪找到的？
Where'd you find 'em?

1221
01:53:06,529 --> 01:53:08,359
差不多一哩之外
'Bout a mile back yonder.

1222
01:53:09,498 --> 01:53:11,863
- 是强尼霍马兹 - 那是杰克帕金
That's Johnny Hormatz. And Jack Perkins.

1223
01:53:15,174 --> 01:53:17,164
在搞什么？野餐吗？
What the hell is this? A picnic?

1224
01:53:17,343 --> 01:53:18,809
- 印地安人杀了我们的几个人
The Indians got a couple of our men--

1225
01:53:18,876 --> 01:53:22,276
- 先生，你之前是工头…
Mister, you were the foreman here. Now you're a tracklayer.

1226
01:53:22,350 --> 01:53:24,249
现在你沦为小工 大家全给我回去工作！
Now get back to work, all of you!

1227
01:53:24,318 --> 01:53:25,375
快点！
Move it!

1228
01:53:25,720 --> 01:53:26,777
快！
Fast!

1229
01:53:27,556 --> 01:53:28,749
- 你 - 是的
-You. -Yes, sir?

1230
01:53:28,824 --> 01:53:32,623
你现在成了工头 直到我找到更棒的人取代你
You're the new foreman, till I find somebody better. Now get 'em at it!

1231
01:53:32,696 --> 01:53:34,458
- 遵命 - 快叫他们做事！
-Wait a minute. -Move it!

1232
01:53:32,764 --> 01:53:34,725
- 等一下 - 快点！

1233
01:53:34,965 --> 01:53:36,955
你叫杰梭罗史都瓦特？
Is your name Jethro Stuart?

1234
01:53:39,370 --> 01:53:43,203
好，快点工作！
Mr. Jethro Stuart, you're hired to hunt buffalo to feed these men...

1235
01:53:39,396 --> 01:53:43,025
杰梭罗史都瓦特先生 你的工作是去猎水牛喂这些工人…

1236
01:53:43,276 --> 01:53:46,267
不是阻挠他们做事 你干嘛把尸体带回来？
...not to stop their work. Why'd you bring these bodies here?

1237
01:53:46,913 --> 01:53:50,211
我想铁路公司的人或许会有兴趣
They're railroaders. I thought somebody on the railroad might be interested.

1238
01:53:50,251 --> 01:53:52,741
我就是铁路公司的人 我一点兴趣都没有
I'm the railroad, and I'm not interested.

1239
01:53:53,422 --> 01:53:56,720
你应该就地埋掉 然后找出杀他们的印地安人
You should've buried 'em, then tracked down the Indians who did it.

1240
01:53:57,695 --> 01:54:02,427
金先生，就像你说的 我的工作是猎水牛
Mr. King, like you said, I was hired to hunt, not to dig graves or fight Indians.

1241
01:54:00,125 --> 01:54:03,253
不是挖坟墓 或去对付印地安人

1242
01:54:03,536 --> 01:54:07,631
这些人多半是退伍军人 几具尸体应该不会 让他们感到不适吧
Those fellas are mostly old soldiers. Two dead men shouldn't bother 'em much.

1243
01:54:05,297 --> 01:54:07,799


1244
01:54:07,906 --> 01:54:11,932
除了工作，我不要他们有其他想法 你了解吗？
I don't want anything in their thick skulls but their work. Do you understand?

1245
01:54:12,012 --> 01:54:15,276
把那些尸体弄掉 开始去追查涉嫌的印地安人
Now get rid of those bodies and start trackin' those Indians.

1246
01:54:15,384 --> 01:54:18,910
你真是贵人多忘事，金先生 我的工作是猎水牛
You keep forgettin', Mr. King, my job's buffalo.

1247
01:54:21,924 --> 01:54:23,356
已经不是了
It was buffalo.

1248
01:54:23,963 --> 01:54:26,453
去找会计，把你的工时算一算
Go to the paymaster and draw your time.

1249
01:54:26,598 --> 01:54:29,031
刚才那个工头你并没开除他
That foreman fella, you didn't fire him.

1250
01:54:29,268 --> 01:54:31,929
你只是降他的职 因为你需要他
You just took him down a peg 'cause you needed him.

1251
01:54:32,005 --> 01:54:34,404
现在谁来负责猎水牛？你吗？
Who's gonna shoot buffalo? You?

1252
01:55:06,650 --> 01:55:08,708
- 那是什么鬼？ - 牛奶
-What the devil is that? -Milk.

1253
01:55:09,520 --> 01:55:10,611
牛奶？
Milk?

1254
01:55:11,655 --> 01:55:14,088
看来我退伍之后 军队改变了不少
The Army must've changed since I was in it.

1255
01:55:14,358 --> 01:55:16,951
- 我刚到，我饿了 - 是吗？
-I just rode in. I'm hungry. -You are, huh?

1256
01:55:18,865 --> 01:55:21,332
但你宁可看他们吃东西
But you'd rather watch them than eat.

1257
01:55:21,568 --> 01:55:23,091
- 是这样吗？ - 是的
-Is that it? -That's it.

1258
01:55:23,437 --> 01:55:26,337
希望你是全力以赴在保护这条铁路
I wish you were as eager to protect this railroad.

1259
01:55:27,007 --> 01:55:30,339
你有没有听说 今天有两个人被杀？
Did you get any word about the two men who where killed today?

1260
01:55:30,412 --> 01:55:33,005
我找到阿拉巴赫族的人 并和他们酋长谈过
I tracked the Arapahoes and talked to the chief.

1261
01:55:33,716 --> 01:55:36,479
那两个人擅入禁区一哩内
They were a mile off the right-of-way where they had no business...

1262
01:55:36,554 --> 01:55:38,350
他们无权酒醉跑进那里 调戏印地安女人
...drunk and chasin' squaws.

1263
01:55:38,957 --> 01:55:41,857
- 他们和印地安人一样有错 - 是这样吗？
It was as much their fault as it was the Indians'.

1264
01:55:42,829 --> 01:55:46,889
阿兵哥，你的任务是对抗印地安人 不是和他们和谈
Well, soldier boy, your job is to fight Indians, not to agree with 'em.

1265
01:55:47,399 --> 01:55:51,027
金先生，当时有两百个阿拉巴赫人 我只有二十名手下
Mr. King, there were 200 Arapahoes and I had 20 men.

1266
01:55:52,041 --> 01:55:53,439
对我而言…
Now, to me...

1267
01:55:53,776 --> 01:55:55,868
和谈是比对抗更为明智的选择
...agreein' seemed wiser than fightin'.

1268
01:55:55,978 --> 01:55:57,035
对你而言？
To you, huh?

1269
01:55:58,381 --> 01:56:01,645
或许我应该给上校派一份电报过去
You know, I might just send off a wire to the colonel.

1270
01:56:02,086 --> 01:56:03,552
他或许不会同意你的做法
He may not agree.

1271
01:56:05,457 --> 01:56:07,822
我已经呈报过 他也同意了
I already reported it. He does agree.

1272
01:56:41,438 --> 01:56:43,701
讯息已接收并知晓… 士兵
Acknowledged and understood. Sergeant.

1273
01:56:44,440 --> 01:56:45,599
有麻烦吗，长官？
Trouble, sir?

1274
01:56:50,915 --> 01:56:52,074
我不知道
I don't know.

1275
01:56:52,652 --> 01:56:53,913
嘿，队长
Hey, Lieutenant.

1276
01:56:56,656 --> 01:56:58,623
我刚收到讯息 印地安人打算发动攻击
I just got a message the Indians are up to something.

1277
01:56:58,693 --> 01:57:00,626
你可知情？
Do you know anything about it?

1278
01:57:00,661 --> 01:57:03,527
酋长说铁路公司毁约
The chief says the railroad's busted the agreement.

1279
01:57:03,633 --> 01:57:06,999
要改变路径 得从亚拉帕霍人的狩猎区经过
They've changed the route and are comin' through the Arapahoe huntin' grounds.

1280
01:57:07,070 --> 01:57:09,629
- 你确定酋长没说错？ - 确定
-You sure the chief's right? -Plenty sure.

1281
01:57:09,739 --> 01:57:11,865
他们已经准备开战了
They're getting the warpaint ready.

1282
01:57:15,649 --> 01:57:17,741
你的意思是说…
Can you stand there and tell me...

1283
01:57:17,816 --> 01:57:21,751
一点小改变就会让 阿拉巴赫族少一头水牛…
...that one little change is gonna cost the Arapahoes one buffalo.

1284
01:57:21,888 --> 01:57:23,684
- 或者甚至少一头野兔？ - 金先生…
-Or even one jackrabbit? -Mr. King!

1285
01:57:24,125 --> 01:57:27,491
他们或许会觉得有所出入 但没有人要伤害他们啊！
They can be made to see it differently. Who's hurting 'em?

1286
01:57:27,730 --> 01:57:30,755
铁路到底是啥玩意？ 只不过是两条铁道和一个大哨子
What's a railroad anyway? Two tracks and a whistle.

1287
01:57:31,701 --> 01:57:35,067
他们怕的不是铁道 而是铁道即将带来的东西
It's not the tracks they're afraid of. It's what the tracks bring.

1288
01:57:35,140 --> 01:57:38,006
水牛猎人猎杀他们的畜兽
The buffalo hunters slaughtering off their herds.

1289
01:57:38,143 --> 01:57:40,007
接下来拓荒者抵达之后…
And then the settlers coming in.

1290
01:57:40,078 --> 01:57:42,978
那到等到何时？ 二十，三十年之后？
And when will that be? Twenty, 30 years, maybe?

1291
01:57:43,049 --> 01:57:44,845
那个时候我们全都死了
By then, we'll all be dead.

1292
01:57:45,553 --> 01:57:47,679
现在我们只要横跨这片土地
Right now we're just crossing the land.

1293
01:57:47,755 --> 01:57:51,246
就这样，在我们有生之年 阿拉巴赫族的土地不会有事
That's all. Land that's safe to the Arapahoes for our lifetime.

1294
01:57:51,759 --> 01:57:54,784
你去和他们谈
Now, you go talk to 'em. Smoke a peacepipe with 'em.

1295
01:57:53,149 --> 01:57:56,111
和他们抽抽和平烟 随他们怎样都好

1296
01:57:56,101 --> 01:57:58,330
主要是和他们拟定新合约
Just get 'em to make a new agreement.

1297
01:58:00,104 --> 01:58:03,072
那是你的任务不是吗？ 维持和平？
That's your job, isn't it? Keeping the peace?

1298
01:58:05,042 --> 01:58:07,009
我会维持和平的，金先生
I'll keep the peace, Mr. King...

1299
01:58:07,280 --> 01:58:09,110
但你也必须信守承诺
...if you keep your promise.

1300
01:58:18,195 --> 01:58:20,594
听说你姓罗林 你是俄亥俄州人
Hear your name's Rawlings and you're from Ohio.

1301
01:58:20,664 --> 01:58:23,655
你爸该不会是叫奈勒斯罗林吧？
Your pa's name couldn't be Linus Rawlings, could it?

1302
01:58:23,901 --> 01:58:25,333
- 是的 - 我认识他
-Could be. -Knew him.

1303
01:58:25,937 --> 01:58:27,096
我是杰梭罗史都瓦特
Jethro Stuart.

1304
01:58:27,340 --> 01:58:29,569
- 他曾经提过你 - “曾经”？
-He used to speak of you. -Used to?

1305
01:58:30,109 --> 01:58:31,837
爸在沙罗殉身
Pa was killed at Shiloh.

1306
01:58:33,146 --> 01:58:34,703
请坐，史都瓦特先生
Sit down, Mr. Stuart.

1307
01:58:36,282 --> 01:58:38,579
至少强过死在锄犁后面
Well, better than dyin' behind a plow.

1308
01:58:38,821 --> 01:58:41,880
我曾经试图安定过一年
I tried it. Settled down for a year once.

1309
01:58:42,291 --> 01:58:44,383
害我少了十年寿命
It took ten years off my life.

1310
01:58:46,963 --> 01:58:48,020
你妈妈…
Your ma....

1311
01:58:49,100 --> 01:58:53,035
她一定很特别 才能让奈勒斯甘心定下来
She must've been somethin' real special gettin' old Linus to stay put.

1312
01:58:54,240 --> 01:58:56,901
她是的，史都瓦特先生 她很特别
She was, Mr. Stuart. Very special.

1313
01:58:57,977 --> 01:58:59,000
这个老奈勒斯…
Old Linus.

1314
01:58:59,948 --> 01:59:04,213
有两午时间 你爸和我曾经一起捕兽皮…
Two years runnin' once, your pa and me trapped together. Up along the Wannakee.

1315
01:59:02,594 --> 01:59:04,512
就在望纳比那边

1316
01:59:04,385 --> 01:59:05,874
抓到好多海狸 多到必须将他们尾巴绑起来…
We got ourselves so many beaver...

1317
01:59:05,955 --> 01:59:09,014
才能把它们拖下山
...we had to tie 'em tail-to-tail just to drag 'em down the mountain.

1318
01:59:09,094 --> 01:59:12,028
有一哩长呢 那些海狸皮毛
Over a mile long it was, that line of beaver pelts.

1319
01:59:12,430 --> 01:59:16,422
史都瓦特先生，我父亲可以把事实 加油添醋讲成六种版本
Mr. Stuart, my father could take the truth and stretch it about six ways.

1320
01:59:17,002 --> 01:59:18,764
你的口气和他好像
You sound just like him.

1321
01:59:20,074 --> 01:59:22,268
我想你这番话应该是赞美的意思
I'll take it you meant that kindly.

1322
01:59:22,844 --> 01:59:25,641
我可不敢随便说你是个骗子
Well, I'd think twice before I called you a liar.

1323
01:59:26,047 --> 01:59:28,344
提到骗子 我要问你一下…
Tell me somethin', talkin' about liars:

1324
01:59:28,950 --> 01:59:32,783
为什么奈勒斯的儿子会和 麦克金这种人在一起？
Why would a son of old Linus get mixed up with a man like Mike King?

1325
01:59:34,660 --> 01:59:36,058
我知道你的意思
I know what you mean.

1326
01:59:36,194 --> 01:59:38,286
但麦克金并不代表铁路
But Mike King isn't the railroad.

1327
01:59:39,330 --> 01:59:41,160
我不认为他知道这一点
I don't think he knows that.

1328
01:59:41,702 --> 01:59:43,862
他要把路线改回去，是吧？
He's changin' the route back, is he?

1329
01:59:44,270 --> 01:59:45,258
没有
No.

1330
01:59:46,806 --> 01:59:47,794
我知道…
I know.

1331
01:59:47,909 --> 01:59:50,968
但他会不择手段 只为了比《中太平洋公司》抢先一天
But he'd do anything to gain a day on the Central Pacific.

1332
01:59:51,079 --> 01:59:53,342
他不是笨蛋，
But he's not a fool. He doesn't want a war.

1333
01:59:53,416 --> 01:59:55,349
他不想开战 阿拉巴赫族也不想
And neither do the Arapahoes.

1334
01:59:56,386 --> 01:59:58,979
我想我应该可以说服他们同意 改变铁道路线…
I think I could get them to agree to this change in route if...

1335
01:59:59,056 --> 02:00:01,683
如果我可以和他们坐下来好好聊一聊
...I could just sit down and talk with them for a while.

1336
02:00:01,757 --> 02:00:04,156
- 你要怎么做？ - 这便是问题所在
-How're you gonna get 'em to do it? -That's just it.

1337
02:00:04,498 --> 02:00:07,989
我需要一个懂他们语言 而且他们能信赖的人
I need somebody that knows the language and that they trust.

1338
02:00:09,102 --> 02:00:12,366
你有没有认识像这样的人 史都瓦特先生？
You wouldn't happen to know someone like that, would you, Mr. Stuart?

1339
02:00:16,212 --> 02:00:19,510
你老爸设陷阱的手段无人能比…
Your pa could set a trap like no man I ever come across.

1340
02:00:20,250 --> 02:00:22,945
慢慢引他们上钩，然后…
Just coax 'em on, and wham!

1341
02:00:40,275 --> 02:00:44,040
你最好做点表态动作 好让他确定你不会食言
You'd better do somethin', so he'll know you're pledgin' your word.

1342
02:01:30,173 --> 02:01:34,040
那该死的哨声听起来好像 命运索魂令
That blame whistle's like the crack of doom from all that's natural.

1343
02:01:34,445 --> 02:01:37,538
我妈总认为人应该在土地上 留点记号
My ma felt a man oughta make his scratch on the land...

1344
02:01:38,049 --> 02:01:41,017
在离开时 留下不同风貌
...and leave it a little different than when he come.

1345
02:01:41,154 --> 02:01:43,951
总之，谢谢你帮我处理酋长的事
Anyway, thanks for fixin' things with the chief.

1346
02:01:44,024 --> 02:01:45,547
我？我可没处理什么事
Me? I fixed nothin'.

1347
02:01:45,626 --> 02:01:48,423
我只是代你传话罢了 并不代表能事成
You put the words in my mouth but that won't make 'em come true.

1348
02:01:48,497 --> 02:01:52,262
杰梭罗，我说过我必须维持和平
I said what I had to, to keep the peace. I know there's a risk.

1349
02:01:52,334 --> 02:01:54,824
- 我知道会有风险 - 风险？
Risks? Maybe you don't understand.

1350
02:01:53,473 --> 02:01:55,475
或许你并不明白

1351
02:01:55,605 --> 02:01:58,573
你刚才已经郑重承诺你的话
You pledged your word back there. Not mine, not the Army's...

1352
02:01:58,644 --> 02:02:00,167
那不是我的，不是军队的 也不是铁路公司的话
...not the railroad's.

1353
02:02:00,245 --> 02:02:02,474
是你告诉他们 他们能够保有原来的狩猎之地
It was your word that told 'em they'd keep their huntin' grounds.

1354
02:02:02,547 --> 02:02:03,843
- 我认为他们会的
I think they will.

1355
02:02:03,949 --> 02:02:06,917
- 我认为你好比把头伸出去…
I think you've got your neck stuck out like a prairie chicken...

1356
02:02:06,985 --> 02:02:09,646
像一只待宰的鸡 等着人来宰你的头
...waitin' for one side or the other to chop it off.

1357
02:02:09,892 --> 02:02:12,359
你老爸当初和我一再地被人 赶出荒地…
Your pa and me got kicked out of one territory after another...

1358
02:02:12,427 --> 02:02:16,089
一堆人蜂拥而至 终结狩猎，建设乡镇
...with people pourin' in, killin' off game, puttin' up towns....

1359
02:02:16,232 --> 02:02:17,630
这股风潮是不会停止的
It ain't gonna stop.

1360
02:02:18,300 --> 02:02:22,326
你的合约将会被人破坏 我不想留在这里看它发生
Your treaty's gonna get broken and I don't wanna be around to see it happen.

1361
02:02:22,572 --> 02:02:24,971
等你受够了之后再来找我吧
Look me up when you get your bellyful.

1362
02:02:25,244 --> 02:02:27,370
- 你要去哪？ - 回去山上
-Where you goin'? -Back to the mountains.

1363
02:02:27,445 --> 02:02:30,971
与世隔绝的山上 完全没有人烟的地方
To the high lonesome where there ain't no people at all yet.

1364
02:02:31,952 --> 02:02:32,918
再会
So long.

1365
02:02:40,597 --> 02:02:44,896
现在《中太平洋公司》已穿越 喜耶亚山区的屏障…
By now the Central Pacific had broken through the wall of the High Sierras...

1366
02:02:45,102 --> 02:02:48,537
疲惫不堪地往东经过 平坦的内华达州
...and was straining eastward across the flatlands of Nevada.

1367
02:02:49,573 --> 02:02:53,406
而《联合太平洋公司》 多亏与印地安人之间的长期和平相处…
While the Union Pacific, thanks to its long peace with the Indians...

1368
02:02:53,547 --> 02:02:57,175
才能够轻松面对庞大压力 士气高昂地朝另一方向前进
...was able to keep up pressure just as avidly in the opposite direction.

1369
02:03:13,005 --> 02:03:15,996
这场竞争十分刺激 但也同时花费不少…
The competition was exciting, but also costly...

1370
02:03:16,541 --> 02:03:20,943
两家公司都迫不及待想从 已经架设好的铁道开始赚取获利
...and both companies were itching to earn money from tracks already laid.

1371
02:03:35,634 --> 02:03:38,261
- 马儿情况还好吧，杰克？ - 我刚骑时不太好
-Did the horses ride all right, Jake? -No better than I did.

1372
02:03:38,337 --> 02:03:42,534
必须让他们休息一天 才能出发去猎兔子或水牛
We'll have to rest 'em a day before we can start huntin' rabbits, much less buffalo.

1373
02:03:42,641 --> 02:03:44,665
立刻牵他们去喝水
Let's get 'em to water right away.

1374
02:03:44,779 --> 02:03:46,769
你说不会有水牛猎人来
You say no buffalo hunter come.

1375
02:03:47,348 --> 02:03:48,644
白人都是骗子
White man, liar.

1376
02:03:49,151 --> 02:03:50,708
我们再也不替你们侦察了
We scout for you no more!

1377
02:03:57,528 --> 02:03:59,154
你说我们活着的时候都不会来
Not in our lifetime, you said.

1378
02:03:59,229 --> 02:04:02,664
结果跑来一堆水牛猎人和拓荒者
And there they are. The buffalo slaughterers and the settlers.

1379
02:04:03,602 --> 02:04:06,001
好啦，是比我预料得早
All right, it's sooner than I figured.

1380
02:04:06,406 --> 02:04:09,670
但铁路公司没钱了 他们需要钱继续运作
But the railroad's broke. They need money to keep movin' on.

1381
02:04:09,710 --> 02:04:12,041
没有人力就没有钱 没有钱就没有铁路
No people, no money. No money, no railroad.

1382
02:04:12,113 --> 02:04:15,172
- 就这么简单 - 那阿拉巴赫族呢？
-It's as simple as that, Lieutenant. -What about the Arapahoes?

1383
02:04:15,248 --> 02:04:18,648
瞧瞧这些人 有半数的人都是从欧洲来的
Take a look at those people. Half of 'em straight from Europe.

1384
02:04:19,323 --> 02:04:21,119
他们会很辛苦 但他们能熬过的
They'll have a rough time but they'll make it.

1385
02:04:21,191 --> 02:04:23,522
你知道他们为何能熬过？
And do you wanna know why they'll make it?

1386
02:04:23,594 --> 02:04:26,289
因为他们肯变通 肯改变自己的生活方式
Because they're willing to change their ways.

1387
02:04:27,366 --> 02:04:30,266
阿拉巴赫族也得改变生活方式才行 如果不肯，他们就完蛋了
The Arapahoes will have to change, too. If they don't, they're finished.

1388
02:04:30,337 --> 02:04:33,134
我知道他们必须改变 将来有天这片土地将被占领…
I know they have to change and some day the land'll be taken over...

1389
02:04:33,207 --> 02:04:35,834
被这些农夫的城镇和牲畜占领
...by these farmers with their towns and their cattle.

1390
02:04:36,109 --> 02:04:37,507
可是不能像这样
But, not like this.

1391
02:04:37,580 --> 02:04:40,707
他们没有必要被人摆弄 而我不想被卷入其中
They don't have to be double-crossed, and I don't have to be a part of it!

1392
02:04:40,783 --> 02:04:42,409
你不想，队长？
You don't, Lieutenant?

1393
02:04:43,385 --> 02:04:45,579
你忘记你身上这套制服了？
Aren't you forgetting that uniform?

1394
02:04:45,689 --> 02:04:48,156
没错，金先生，我是想忘掉
That's right, Mr. King, I'm forgetting it!

1395
02:04:48,227 --> 02:04:51,389
如果军队在这里没有任何权限 那我现在就要辞职
If the Army hasn't got any authority out here, I'm resigning. And, now!

1396
02:04:51,497 --> 02:04:53,726
我不认为那样对阿拉巴赫族 有任何帮助
I don't see how that's gonna help the Arapahoes.

1397
02:04:53,800 --> 02:04:55,357
没有任何事能帮助他们
Nothing'll help 'em.

1398
02:04:55,534 --> 02:04:57,398
但也没有任何事情能阻止他们
But nothing's gonna stop 'em.

1399
02:05:27,876 --> 02:05:29,274
印地安人来袭！
Indian attack!

1400
02:05:30,231 --> 02:05:31,983
印地安人来袭！找掩护！

1401
02:05:42,563 --> 02:05:43,893
你看看…
Take a good look!

1402
02:05:44,331 --> 02:05:47,663
你想要战争，你可如愿了 我希望你是第一个赔上性命的人
You wanted a war, and you got one. I hope you're the first man killed in it.

1403
02:05:47,769 --> 02:05:49,759
把篷车调头！
Turn those wagons over!

1404
02:06:12,201 --> 02:06:14,691
对准领先的马匹开枪 先拿下酋长！
Shoot for the lead horses. Sergeant, take over.

1405
02:06:14,870 --> 02:06:16,336
罗林，你用这个
Rawlings, try that.

1406
02:06:25,784 --> 02:06:27,944
印地安人故意让水牛狂奔逃窜
The Indians are stampeding the buffalo.

1407
02:06:28,187 --> 02:06:29,653
卑鄙小人！ 来吧
Dirty skunks! Come on!

1408
02:08:47,498 --> 02:08:49,761
我告诉过你不会有战争
I told you there'd be no war.

1409
02:08:50,938 --> 02:08:52,063
瞧瞧他们
Look at 'em.

1410
02:08:52,572 --> 02:08:53,731
他们撤退了
They've quit.

1411
02:08:54,807 --> 02:08:56,068
他们会再回来的
They'll be back.

1412
02:08:57,143 --> 02:09:01,909
他们派来野兽来杀死 他们称为“铁马”的怪兽
They just sent a bunch of animals to kill an animal they call the "Iron Horse".

1413
02:09:01,984 --> 02:09:04,110
但那怪兽仍在，可不是？
Well, it's still standin', isn't it?

1414
02:09:04,688 --> 02:09:06,484
没有任何事情能阻止它
And nothin's gonna stop it.

1415
02:09:26,749 --> 02:09:28,773
你看到那样 你的日子还过得下去吗？
You think you can live with that?

1416
02:09:30,019 --> 02:09:32,612
我可以与这情况共生共亡！
I can live with it, or I can die with it.

1417
02:09:32,754 --> 02:09:33,879
你听看看…
Just listen!

1418
02:09:34,759 --> 02:09:36,453
你这样还能过得下去吗？
You can live with that?

1419
02:09:37,829 --> 02:09:38,886
那个？
That?

1420
02:09:39,130 --> 02:09:40,596
那才不是哭声
That ain't cryin'.

1421
02:09:41,067 --> 02:09:42,966
那只是新生命继续存活的声音
That's just new life goin' on.

1422
02:09:49,077 --> 02:09:53,035
把这女人扶起来 然后把其他受伤的人抬进帐篷里
Pick up this woman and put the rest of the engine in the shed.

1423
02:09:58,656 --> 02:10:02,091
嘿，马文…剩下的人回去工作！ 我们还得继续造铁路！
The rest of you, back to work. We've got a railroad to build.

1424
02:09:59,041 --> 02:10:02,128


1425
02:10:55,347 --> 02:10:57,099
这个嘛…

1426
02:10:57,533 --> 02:10:59,864
看来你终于已经受够了
It looks like you finally got your bellyful.

1427
02:10:59,935 --> 02:11:01,060
哈罗，杰梭罗
Hello, Jethro.

1428
02:11:02,303 --> 02:11:04,065
看来你过得还不错
Appears you're doin' well.

1429
02:11:05,241 --> 02:11:06,673
还可以
Can't complain.

1430
02:11:07,243 --> 02:11:10,837
溪里满满都是海狸 争先恐后挤进陷阱里
Creek's loaded with beavers, fightin' their way into the trap.

1431
02:11:11,750 --> 02:11:13,273
没有白人指使我做事
Ain't no white men lookin' over my shoulder...

1432
02:11:13,352 --> 02:11:15,546
印地安人都对我很友善
...and the Indians are plumb cordial.

1433
02:11:16,555 --> 02:11:19,318
把你的东西放进去 这地方够两个人住的
Toss your stuff in there. Plenty of room for two.

1434
02:11:19,561 --> 02:11:20,584
谢谢
Thanks.

1435
02:11:22,230 --> 02:11:23,560
你就睡在那边
You'll be bunkin' yonder.

1436
02:11:23,631 --> 02:11:26,224
熟悉一下环境 以便待会儿需要什么就可以找到
Better take your bearin's now, so you can find it when you need it.

1437
02:11:26,302 --> 02:11:29,099
你若不习惯我打呼 你明天可以自己盖一间木屋
If you don't like my snorin' you can build your own cabin tomorrow.

1438
02:11:29,172 --> 02:11:30,729
我帮你打点里面
I'll furnish the axe.

1439
02:11:33,112 --> 02:11:34,669
- 谢谢，我只是路过而已
Thanks. I'm just passin' through.

1440
02:11:34,779 --> 02:11:36,040
- 路过去哪？
Through to where?

1441
02:11:36,714 --> 02:11:38,908
你所到之处都是去过的地方
Anywhere you go is like where you've been.

1442
02:11:38,950 --> 02:11:41,747
你在那边受的伤害还不够？
Ain't you lost enough tail feathers back there?

1443
02:11:43,356 --> 02:11:45,016
我是受过一点伤
I've been plucked some.

1444
02:11:46,292 --> 02:11:48,282
但那便是我喜欢这个国家的原因
But that's what I like about this country.

1445
02:11:48,330 --> 02:11:50,820
另一座山丘的草永远都比较绿
There's always greener grass over the next hill.

1446
02:11:51,667 --> 02:11:54,260
打从那该死铁路经过之后 再也不是了
Not no more. Not since that damn railroad come.

1447
02:11:54,638 --> 02:11:57,868
所有牧草都被人管东锁了起来
All the grass is bein' staked out now, with a lock on it.

1448
02:12:00,276 --> 02:12:03,870
或许我得再爬高一点的山丘 才能找到
Maybe I'll just have to climb a little higher hill to find it.

1449
02:12:06,887 --> 02:12:08,353
要不要一起来？
How about comin' along?

1450
02:12:08,622 --> 02:12:09,849
你疯了？
Are you crazy?

1451
02:12:10,891 --> 02:12:14,257
就像印地安人说的： “这些石头和树木都不想搬家”
Like the Indians say, "These rocks and trees around here feel no call to move.

1452
02:12:14,329 --> 02:12:15,795
“凭什么我要搬呢？”
"Why should I?"

1453
02:12:17,233 --> 02:12:19,257
我或许不是印地安人，杰梭罗…
Guess I'm not an Indian, Jethro.

1454
02:12:19,969 --> 02:12:22,095
我也不是石头或树木…
And I'm sure not a rock nor a tree.

1455
02:12:22,942 --> 02:12:25,774
但物以类聚 不管愿不愿意
A man belongs with his own kind, like him or not.

1456
02:13:02,057 --> 02:13:06,356
铁路的来临为沿路的土地 带来了许多改变
The coming of railroads brought changes in the land through which they passed.

1457
02:13:06,497 --> 02:13:10,296
现在成群牛羊聚集 绵延数百哩之长…
Now, immense herds of cattle were driven hundreds of miles to meet the lines...

1458
02:13:10,400 --> 02:13:12,390
朝东边的市集前进
...bound for markets in the East.

1459
02:13:12,904 --> 02:13:15,497
原野上竖立起篱笆 牛羊被圈围起来…
Fences went up, cattle trails were barred...

1460
02:13:16,142 --> 02:13:20,100
畜牧业者和拓荒者之间长久以来 存在着血腥斗争…
...and a long and bloody wrangle began between cattlemen and homesteaders.

1461
02:13:20,748 --> 02:13:24,410
法令是由那些射枪 最快最准的人决定的
The law was in the hands of whoever could shoot fast and straight...

1462
02:13:24,985 --> 02:13:28,511
不过有些人也会执意出面 当法令代言人
...except where there was somebody determined to stand for law.

1463
02:13:29,259 --> 02:13:33,092
有些人看到羊群可能会觉得 很具有田园风光
Others might look on sheep and a shepherd as a pastoral scene.

1464
02:13:35,833 --> 02:13:37,265
但畜牧业者可不这么想
But not the cattleman.

1465
02:13:37,335 --> 02:13:41,361
对他们而言，羊把草吃光 而青草得之不易
To him, sheep destroyed grass, and grass came dear.

1466
02:13:43,076 --> 02:13:45,908
如果某个人的性命 比草还不值钱…
And if a man's life were held cheaper than grass...

1467
02:13:46,045 --> 02:13:49,275
那只会被视为战争死伤 而非触犯杀人罪
...it was considered a casualty of war, not a crime.

1468
02:13:50,085 --> 02:13:51,381
在所有争端事件当中
And, in all this...

1469
02:13:51,520 --> 02:13:54,511
唯一以寡敌众的便是那些佩戴警徽的人
...the man with the star was only one against many.

1470
02:13:56,226 --> 02:13:59,092
但那些非法之徒日子愈来愈难过…
But time was running out for the reckless ones...

1471
02:13:59,164 --> 02:14:02,155
即那些亡命之徒 那些持枪犯案的小子
...the desperadoes, the gallop-and-gunshot boys...

1472
02:14:03,101 --> 02:14:05,933
因为有愈来愈多老百姓 开始要求大家遵行法令
...as more and more citizens demanded respect for the law...

1473
02:14:06,004 --> 02:14:08,938
并以身作则随时回击 以维护法令尊严
...and showed themselves ready to fight to uphold it.

1474
02:14:08,978 --> 02:14:12,378
这些在西部陆续成立的新城镇 都开始梦想…
And the raw new towns that sprung up in the West began to dream...

1475
02:14:12,447 --> 02:14:16,780
有天能成为在金门畔 曾经被视为流氓城市的那个地方
...of becoming as refined as that one-time hooligan city by the Golden Gate.

1476
02:14:17,353 --> 02:14:19,445
旧金山现在变得繁华热闹…
San Francisco was now respectable.

1477
02:14:19,957 --> 02:14:23,551
文明优雅到甚至有人拍卖华厦
So sophisticated, in fact, it even had mansions up for auction.

1478
02:14:24,063 --> 02:14:25,256
两千元！
$2,000.

1479
02:14:25,931 --> 02:14:27,192
两千元！
$2,000.

1480
02:14:28,066 --> 02:14:29,532
那是最后一次出价？
Is that your last bid?

1481
02:14:30,271 --> 02:14:34,206
各位先生女士 这奖杯可是纯黄金打造，还刻着…
Ladies and gentlemen, this trophy is solid gold and fully inscribed.

1482
02:14:35,141 --> 02:14:39,270
“克里夫凡伟伦 旧金山至堪萨斯市铁路公司董事长”
"Mr. Cleve van Valen, President of the San Francisco--Kansas City Railroad."

1483
02:14:40,217 --> 02:14:42,616
这可是他心爱的个人收藏
It's a treasure he held dear to his heart.

1484
02:14:43,187 --> 02:14:46,155
有没有人出价三千买这无价收藏？
Do I hear $3,000 for this priceless possession?

1485
02:14:47,257 --> 02:14:48,883
无价个头啦…
Priceless, my foot.

1486
02:14:49,827 --> 02:14:51,487
我们当初拿它当门挡
We used it for a doorstop.

1487
02:14:52,499 --> 02:14:53,465
- 两千五百元！ - 两千五百元！
$2,500.

1488
02:14:53,533 --> 02:14:55,022
两千五百元！
$2,500.

1489
02:14:55,337 --> 02:14:57,172


1490
02:14:58,506 --> 02:15:00,097
两千五百元？两千五百元卖出！
Sold. $2,500.

1491
02:15:00,843 --> 02:15:02,434
真是令人难过的一天，莉莉丝
It's a sad day, Lilith.

1492
02:15:03,012 --> 02:15:04,035
难过？
Sad?

1493
02:15:04,615 --> 02:15:07,276
我们大赚大花三次财富
We made and spent three fortunes together.

1494
02:15:07,384 --> 02:15:09,112
有什么好难过的？
What's so sad about that?

1495
02:15:09,853 --> 02:15:13,310
如果他再多活久一点 我们有可能再赚再花一次
If he'd lived a little longer we would've made and spent another.

1496
02:15:13,393 --> 02:15:15,917
- 对不起，凡伟伦夫人 - 什么事？
-I beg your pardon, Mrs. van Valen. -What?

1497
02:15:15,994 --> 02:15:17,961
那把椅子已经卖出了，很抱歉
The chair, it's been sold. I'm sorry.

1498
02:15:18,030 --> 02:15:20,554
那就拿去吧 别道歉，尽管拿去
Well then, take it. Quit apologizin' and take it.

1499
02:15:20,634 --> 02:15:21,998
谢谢，夫人
Thank you, madam.

1500
02:15:22,071 --> 02:15:24,470
如果有别的方法可以偿还债务的话…
If there had been some other way to pay off the debts....

1501
02:15:24,539 --> 02:15:26,005
不要紧的
It doesn't matter.

1502
02:15:26,275 --> 02:15:29,266
我有两件东西是没有人能拿走的…
I've got two things no one can ever take from me:

1503
02:15:30,413 --> 02:15:32,880
这个和我在亚利桑那州的土地
This, and my land in Arizona.

1504
02:15:34,186 --> 02:15:36,551
莉莉丝，我不想泼你冷水…
Lilith, I don't want to dash any hopes...

1505
02:15:37,356 --> 02:15:39,482
可是那农场根本不值钱
...but that ranch is nearly worthless.

1506
02:15:39,626 --> 02:15:41,183
但总是一块地，不是吗？
Well, it's there, isn't it?

1507
02:15:41,260 --> 02:15:44,285
是的，但大多数畜牲都卖掉或被偷了
Yes, but most of the cattle have been sold off or stolen.

1508
02:15:44,365 --> 02:15:45,558
- 牛羊再买就是了
I'll get cattle.

1509
02:15:45,633 --> 02:15:47,998
- 你将需要有人帮忙做事- 有人帮你经营农场
You'll need someone to work it and manage it for you.

1510
02:15:48,071 --> 02:15:50,038
- 我会找人的  找谁？
-I'll get that, too. -Who?

1511
02:15:50,906 --> 02:15:53,999
我的侄子 他在当骑警
My nephew. He's a marshal out there somewhere.

1512
02:15:51,018 --> 02:15:55,064


1513
02:15:55,046 --> 02:15:57,707
莉莉丝，你这把年纪 那种日子可能会很辛苦
Lilith, at your age it might be kind of rough.

1514
02:15:59,349 --> 02:16:00,372
辛苦？
Rough?

1515
02:16:01,153 --> 02:16:04,918
我爸妈当初为了寻找土地 在河上航行遇难而死
My ma and pa were killed goin' down the river just lookin' for land.

1516
02:16:06,426 --> 02:16:10,259
我想我多少还是有 普莱斯考特家的遗传
I guess I got a little of that Prescott blood in me after all.

1517
02:16:19,577 --> 02:16:20,565
爸？
Pa?

1518
02:16:21,244 --> 02:16:24,178
莉莉丝姨婆在诺布丘的家 和那一样高吗？
Is Aunt Lilith's house on Nob Hill as high as that?

1519
02:16:26,486 --> 02:16:27,952
我不知道，儿子
I don't know, son.

1520
02:16:28,254 --> 02:16:31,416
待会儿回家，你可以问莉莉丝姨婆 她会告诉你
On our way home you ask your Aunt Lilith. She'll tell you.

1521
02:17:20,822 --> 02:17:23,221
亲爱的？你想你认得出她吗？
Honey? Do you think you'll know her?

1522
02:17:23,658 --> 02:17:24,351
- 什么？
What?

1523
02:17:24,425 --> 02:17:26,824
- 你的莉莉丝阿姨- 你想你可以认得出她吗？
Your Aunt Lilith. Do you think you'll recognize her?

1524
02:17:27,029 --> 02:17:28,086
- 当然
Sure.

1525
02:17:28,230 --> 02:17:30,459
齐伯？怎么回事？
Zeb? What's the matter?

1526
02:17:32,070 --> 02:17:33,058
没事
Nothing.

1527
02:17:33,138 --> 02:17:34,126
走吧
Come on.

1528
02:17:40,711 --> 02:17:42,504
谢谢

1529
02:17:42,671 --> 02:17:45,299
（黄金城交界处）

1530
02:17:47,589 --> 02:17:49,522
- 请问你是莉莉丝姨婆吗？
Ma'am, are you our Great Aunt Lilith?

1531
02:17:49,557 --> 02:17:51,717
- 如果你们是齐伯的孩子，我就是
If you're Zeb's children, I am.

1532
02:17:54,599 --> 02:17:55,587
- 莉莉丝
Lilith.

1533
02:17:56,534 --> 02:17:57,557
- 齐伯
Zeb.

1534
02:17:58,402 --> 02:17:59,868
齐伯罗林
Zeb Rawlings.

1535
02:18:01,207 --> 02:18:02,366
喔，老天
Oh, goodness.

1536
02:18:02,742 --> 02:18:05,733
我一再叮咛自己绝对不准哭的
I swore up and down I wasn't gonna cry.

1537
02:18:06,079 --> 02:18:08,512
你就像妈形容的那么美丽
You're just as pretty as Ma said you was.

1538
02:18:09,383 --> 02:18:11,612
这位是我的太太，茱莉
I'd like you to meet my wife, Julie.

1539
02:18:11,754 --> 02:18:13,277
很高兴认识你
Pleased to meet you.

1540
02:18:13,356 --> 02:18:15,380
我也很高兴认识你
And I'm pleased to meet you, too.

1541
02:18:15,725 --> 02:18:18,090
我简直无法形容我有多开心
I just can't tell you how pleased.

1542
02:18:19,128 --> 02:18:21,857
这是伊芙，我们家的老么
This here's Eve, underneath all the jam.

1543
02:18:22,269 --> 02:18:24,361
- 过来见见山姆 - 山姆？
-Come on and meet Sam now. -Sam?

1544
02:18:24,570 --> 02:18:28,164
山姆是我们的马 他可以一次拉两台篷车喔
Sam's our horse. He could pull two wagons if he wanted.

1545
02:18:28,508 --> 02:18:32,273
喔，对不起，失陪了 我得去见过山姆呢
Well, if you'll excuse me, I have my orders to meet Sam.

1546
02:18:32,313 --> 02:18:33,404
走吧
Come on.

1547
02:18:33,714 --> 02:18:35,305
- 喔，慢一点啊，孩子 - 他在另外一头
Just a minute now, boys.

1548
02:18:35,416 --> 02:18:37,474
- 走吧 - 好的
But he's on the other side. Come on.

1549
02:18:39,722 --> 02:18:42,155
- 走吧 - 等一下
I think this means a whole lot to her.

1550
02:18:39,978 --> 02:18:42,189
我认为这对她意义重大

1551
02:18:42,224 --> 02:18:44,555
你不晓得这对我有多重要…
You have no idea how much it means to me...

1552
02:18:44,796 --> 02:18:47,855
能够安顿下来 过着与世无争的日子
...to be able to settle down to a life of peace and quiet.

1553
02:18:48,799 --> 02:18:50,356
我去拿行李
I'll get the luggage.

1554
02:18:53,784 --> 02:18:55,827
哈罗，各位！

1555
02:18:55,994 --> 02:18:57,746
杰克！

1556
02:18:58,080 --> 02:18:59,164
汤姆

1557
02:18:59,331 --> 02:19:01,041
帕布洛

1558
02:19:11,296 --> 02:19:13,286
齐伯，咱们走吧
Zeb, let's go.

1559
02:19:13,846 --> 02:19:19,935


1560
02:19:15,568 --> 02:19:19,264
骑警，别告诉我你大老远跑来黄金城 是为了来见我？
Don't tell me you come all the way to Gold City just to meet me?

1561
02:19:19,841 --> 02:19:21,364
我根本没想到
I hardly expected it.

1562
02:19:22,876 --> 02:19:25,742
这位是美丽的罗林太太？
And the beautiful Mrs. Rawlings?

1563
02:19:27,184 --> 02:19:28,445
真是无上荣幸
What a pleasure.

1564
02:19:29,318 --> 02:19:33,185
我真嫉妒你，骑警 一个年轻貌美的老婆…
I envy you, Marshal, a well-favored, bright-eyed wife...

1565
02:19:33,691 --> 02:19:36,454
就像太阳一般耀眼灿烂
...just as dazzlin' as that sun up there.

1566
02:19:38,530 --> 02:19:40,963
让人心存感激，可不是？
It makes you almost thankful, don't it?

1567
02:19:41,201 --> 02:19:43,327
让人很想好好活下去
It makes a person wanna live.

1568
02:19:44,704 --> 02:19:45,692
再见
Adios.

1569
02:19:49,979 --> 02:19:51,536
那是查理葛兰特
That's Charlie Gant.

1570
02:19:51,748 --> 02:19:54,215
我以为你说他在蒙大拿州
I thought you said he was in Montana?

1571
02:19:54,417 --> 02:19:55,474
齐伯？
Zeb?

1572
02:19:56,285 --> 02:19:58,684
我只是去拿行李，没事
I'm just gonna get the luggage, that's all.

1573
02:20:08,237 --> 02:20:09,760
你去办入房手续吧，茱莉
See to the rooms, will you, Julie?

1574
02:20:09,838 --> 02:20:12,533
- 普莱斯考特，照顾马 - 好的
-Prescott, take care of the horses. -Yes, sir.

1575
02:20:12,607 --> 02:20:15,006
- 奈勒斯，去帮你妈妈 - 好的
-Linus, help your mother. -Yes, sir.

1576
02:20:22,387 --> 02:20:24,047
什么事不对劲吗，茱莉？
Anything wrong, Julie?

1577
02:20:24,589 --> 02:20:26,749
没…没事
No. No, nothing.

1578
02:20:27,458 --> 02:20:28,617
走吧，伊芙
Come on, Eve.

1579
02:20:36,011 --> 02:20:38,513
- 卢 - 齐伯

1580
02:20:38,606 --> 02:20:39,799
有时间吗？
Got a minute?

1581
02:20:40,277 --> 02:20:41,868
我当然有时间
Of course, I got a minute.

1582
02:20:44,144 --> 02:20:45,646
来…

1583
02:20:45,812 --> 02:20:48,357
我郑重劝告你应该要…

1584
02:20:48,419 --> 02:20:49,908
- 抽雪茄？ - 不，谢谢
-Cigar? -No, thanks.

1585
02:20:51,458 --> 02:20:53,084
有什么事我能帮你呢？
Well, what can I do for you?

1586
02:20:55,295 --> 02:20:56,625
你尽管说吧
Go ahead, name it.

1587
02:20:56,665 --> 02:20:59,098
我今天早上看到葛兰特下火车
I saw Gant get off the train this morning.

1588
02:20:59,767 --> 02:21:01,961
有三个人去接他
There were three men waiting for him.

1589
02:21:05,442 --> 02:21:07,102
那是你跑来的原因，是吧？
That's why you're here, huh?

1590
02:21:08,411 --> 02:21:09,434
没错
That's it.

1591
02:21:12,319 --> 02:21:14,582
我们根本没有任何办法…
Look, there ain't a thing we can do...

1592
02:21:14,754 --> 02:21:18,655
阻止查理葛兰特在这地区的活动
...to keep Charlie Gant from goin' where he wants to in this territory.

1593
02:21:20,093 --> 02:21:22,617
我知道 我知道他的为人…
I know. I know what he was...

1594
02:21:24,031 --> 02:21:25,691
但现在已经结束了
...but that's over now.

1595
02:21:26,703 --> 02:21:28,863
这一切早已结束 当他哥哥…
It was over the day his brother got--

1596
02:21:31,007 --> 02:21:33,634
那天应该两个都杀的 但是…
You should've killed 'em both that day, but....

1597
02:21:34,679 --> 02:21:37,806
但你没有 现在我真的一点办法都没了
Well, you didn't and there ain't a thing I can do about it now.

1598
02:21:37,883 --> 02:21:40,715
他来这里做什么，卢？ 你难道不好奇吗？
What's he doin' here, Lou? Ain't you even curious?

1599
02:21:40,920 --> 02:21:44,377
你要我怎么做？ 拿枪抵住他把他赶出城？
What do you want me to do? Run him out of town at the point of a gun?

1600
02:21:44,459 --> 02:21:47,052
你想我们仍用手枪执行法律？
Do you think it will put the law inside a holster here?

1601
02:21:47,129 --> 02:21:49,688
你看那边，齐伯 那才是法律
Look over there, Zeb. There's the law.

1602
02:21:50,565 --> 02:21:53,032
那些条文规定才是法律…
With all its writs and decrees and....

1603
02:21:54,373 --> 02:21:56,499
- 我们现在隶属巡回法院管辖
We abide by that circuit judge, now.

1604
02:21:56,574 --> 02:21:58,006
- 但在此同时有多少人被杀？
How many get killed meantime?

1605
02:21:58,075 --> 02:22:02,670
没有人被杀 不会有人被杀  达克哈立戴，克兰顿，杨格斯…
Nobody's got killed. Nobody's goin' to. Doc Halliday, the Clantons, the Youngers....

1606
02:22:00,345 --> 02:22:03,598


1607
02:22:03,918 --> 02:22:05,111
- 他们全都死了
They're all gone now.

1608
02:22:05,385 --> 02:22:07,045
- 查理葛兰特并没死
Charlie Gant ain't gone.

1609
02:22:08,924 --> 02:22:11,483
你去弄来拘捕令 我就去抓葛兰特
You get me a warrant. I'll get you Gant.

1610
02:22:12,160 --> 02:22:16,061
卢？明天运送黄金的篷车队 需要三名护卫
Lou, they want three guards in the wagon with the gold shipment tomorrow.

1611
02:22:16,099 --> 02:22:17,087
- 三名？
Three?

1612
02:22:17,167 --> 02:22:19,930
- 是宗大案子，市价超过十万元
This is a big one. Over $100,000 worth.

1613
02:22:20,970 --> 02:22:23,631
我带克雷顿和辛姆斯去，好吧？
I'll take Clayton and Sims with me. All right?

1614
02:22:28,416 --> 02:22:29,211
怎么样？
Well?

1615
02:22:30,083 --> 02:22:31,208
什么怎么样？
Well what?

1616
02:22:32,152 --> 02:22:34,210
那对你不代表任何意义吗？
Doesn't that mean anything to you?

1617
02:22:34,454 --> 02:22:37,445
- 那代表我们需要派三名护卫 - 在火车上！
-It means we put on a three-man guard. -To the train.

1618
02:22:37,994 --> 02:22:39,426
那到时候呢？
What happens then?

1619
02:22:40,463 --> 02:22:42,953
我们这里每个月都会运送黄金出去
You know there's gold goin' out of here every month or so.

1620
02:22:43,067 --> 02:22:46,058
自从杰西詹姆士被杀之后 再没有火车被劫事件
There hasn't been a train robbery since Jesse James was killed.

1621
02:22:47,809 --> 02:22:50,812
如果律师们需要私下会谈 我们可以谈一下

1622
02:22:50,979 --> 02:22:52,481
齐伯

1623
02:22:53,846 --> 02:22:55,904
我不想惹任何麻烦
I don't want any trouble here, now.

1624
02:22:55,982 --> 02:22:57,972
咱们是很久的朋友了
We've been friends a long time.

1625
02:22:58,587 --> 02:22:59,746
身为朋友…
As a friend...

1626
02:23:00,789 --> 02:23:02,722
我想请你离开这里
...l'd like you to leave town.

1627
02:23:24,954 --> 02:23:26,784
孩子们，给我过来！
Boys, get back from there!

1628
02:23:30,193 --> 02:23:31,887
你自己往下看
Look down there, son.

1629
02:23:32,097 --> 02:23:34,496
你知道这底下有多深吗？
Do you know how deep that shaft is?

1630
02:23:34,832 --> 02:23:36,662
有一千尺深
That's 1,000 foot deep.

1631
02:23:36,834 --> 02:23:38,960
你知道一千尺有多深吗？
Do you know how deep 1,000 foot is?

1632
02:23:40,541 --> 02:23:43,941
如果把两百个弟弟摆在你肩膀上…
If you had 200 brothers, all standin' on your shoulders...

1633
02:23:44,110 --> 02:23:45,974
- 你还是看不到最上面
...you wouldn't be able to see over the top.

1634
02:23:46,048 --> 02:23:47,514
- 那我不就被压扁了！
I'd be squished.

1635
02:23:48,216 --> 02:23:50,877
走吧，我带你们去看发动机
Come on. I'll show you boys the donkey engine.

1636
02:23:57,127 --> 02:23:59,788
你们先过去 我马上就来
You boys go ahead. I'll be along in a minute.

1637
02:24:02,936 --> 02:24:06,336
（黄金城金矿）听说你跑去找当地骑警谈我的事
I hear you've been talkin' to the local marshal about me.

1638
02:24:03,218 --> 02:24:06,721


1639
02:24:08,675 --> 02:24:10,335
- 此举可真友善
Would you call that friendly?

1640
02:24:10,546 --> 02:24:12,843
- 我从不认为我们的关系是友善的
I never considered us exactly friendly.

1641
02:24:13,082 --> 02:24:14,878
我不喜欢你，骑警
I don't like you, Marshal.

1642
02:24:15,352 --> 02:24:18,912
我不喜欢你们这种人在这国家 所做的一切
I don't like what you and your kind are doin' to this country.

1643
02:24:19,789 --> 02:24:21,346
我不想惹麻烦
I don't want any trouble.

1644
02:24:22,061 --> 02:24:25,257
可是你执意要用从前的标准来看 就你和我？
You wanna put things on the old basis, just you and me?

1645
02:24:26,698 --> 02:24:27,789
那无所谓
That's fine.

1646
02:24:28,969 --> 02:24:31,630
我不打算和你争执，葛兰特
I'm not gonna get in a fight with you, Gant.

1647
02:24:32,907 --> 02:24:35,170
那你是想要和平罗，骑警？
It's peace you want, Marshal?

1648
02:24:35,745 --> 02:24:36,733
和平？
Peace?

1649
02:24:37,380 --> 02:24:39,370
我只知道一种和平
There's only one kind I know of.

1650
02:24:40,782 --> 02:24:42,840
就是我哥哥得到的那种
That's the kind my brother's got.

1651
02:24:43,122 --> 02:24:46,750
你哥哥的遭遇并没有让你 学到太多教训，是吧？
What happened to your brother didn't teach you very much, did it?

1652
02:24:47,092 --> 02:24:48,388
放轻松，骑警…
Easy, Marshal.

1653
02:24:49,695 --> 02:24:51,389
佛洛依从未出过差错…
Floyd never made mistakes...

1654
02:24:51,697 --> 02:24:53,926
除了那次他误信你…
...except the one time he trusted you.

1655
02:24:55,002 --> 02:24:57,060
让你成了漏网之鱼
And you're the one that got away.

1656
02:25:00,675 --> 02:25:04,132
总有一天 我会去府上好好拜访你们
One of these days I'm likely to pay you Rawlings' a little visit.

1657
02:25:31,014 --> 02:25:33,225
快点！走吧！

1658
02:25:33,391 --> 02:25:35,727
把黄金箱子抬上来！

1659
02:25:35,894 --> 02:25:38,021
很多黄金

1660
02:25:38,188 --> 02:25:40,774
快点，继续搬，各位！

1661
02:25:43,151 --> 02:25:44,486
齐伯？

1662
02:25:44,698 --> 02:25:46,062
卢莱姆西来了
Lou Ramsey's here.

1663
02:25:48,865 --> 02:25:50,492
卢

1664
02:25:51,073 --> 02:25:53,700
- 我警告过你，齐伯 - 什么事？
-I warned you, Zeb. -What is it?

1665
02:25:54,144 --> 02:25:56,111
葛兰特昨晚跑来找我
Gant came to see me last night.

1666
02:25:56,415 --> 02:25:59,144
说你试图找他麻烦
He said you tried to start some trouble with him.

1667
02:25:59,853 --> 02:26:01,114
你相信他？
You believe him?

1668
02:26:01,387 --> 02:26:04,822
我告诉你，齐伯 你要惹麻烦，到你自己的地盘去搞！
I'm tellin' you, Zeb, you take your trouble to your own territory.

1669
02:26:04,857 --> 02:26:06,881
我这里不要有任何麻烦
I don't want any more of it here.

1670
02:26:09,732 --> 02:26:12,700
不会有任何麻烦，卢 葛兰特走了
There won't be any more trouble, Lou. Gant's gone.

1671
02:26:13,703 --> 02:26:15,966
今天一大早就离开出城了
He rode out of here early this mornin'.

1672
02:26:16,339 --> 02:26:17,327
和谁？
With who?

1673
02:26:17,375 --> 02:26:18,705
他的道上兄弟
His gang.

1674
02:26:19,877 --> 02:26:23,334
他们现在应该在 这里和金曼之间的某个地方…
They should be somewhere between here and Kingman...

1675
02:26:24,383 --> 02:26:26,043
等火车出现
...waitin' on that train.

1676
02:26:26,118 --> 02:26:28,108
你别想唬我，齐伯
You don't fool me for a minute, Zeb.

1677
02:26:28,189 --> 02:26:30,850
你并不是想破抢案 你是想抓葛兰特
You're not lookin' for a robbery, you're lookin' for Gant.

1678
02:26:30,958 --> 02:26:34,120
你身上仍有他射你的子弹 那是在德州
You still carry lead where he shot you. That was Texas.

1679
02:26:34,394 --> 02:26:37,362
还有在奥克拉荷马你射杀佛洛依 现在换这件事！
And Oklahoma, where you killed Floyd. And now this.

1680
02:26:39,970 --> 02:26:41,334
很抱歉，茱莉…
I'm sorry, Julie...

1681
02:26:42,173 --> 02:26:45,073
我们局里不要和这件事有关
...but I don't want my office to be any part of this.

1682
02:26:56,758 --> 02:26:59,185
齐伯，孩子们已经把东西都准备好了
The boys have got the team hitched.

1684
02:26:59,762 --> 02:27:00,887
我知道
I know.

1685
02:27:01,196 --> 02:27:03,095
差不多时候该走了
It's almost time to go.

1686
02:27:07,485 --> 02:27:09,237
齐伯？

1687
02:27:34,073 --> 02:27:36,097
- 茱莉 - 没有人要你去对付葛兰特
No one's askin' you to face Gant.

1688
02:27:36,175 --> 02:27:37,607
没有人逼你
No one's makin' you.

1689
02:27:38,177 --> 02:27:41,168
我们可以马上离开这里 我们可以忘掉这一切
We could ride out of here right now. We could forget it.

1690
02:27:45,019 --> 02:27:47,486
或许你有什么事情没告诉我
Maybe there's somethin' you haven't told me.

1691
02:27:48,957 --> 02:27:50,116
是吗，齐伯？
Is there, Zeb?

1692
02:27:54,933 --> 02:27:56,490
我求你别去
I'm askin' you not to go.

1693
02:27:58,335 --> 02:27:59,460
求求你
Please.

1694
02:28:00,406 --> 02:28:01,838
别去
Don't go.

1695
02:28:04,078 --> 02:28:05,408
对不起，茱莉…
Sorry, Julie.

1696
02:28:23,200 --> 02:28:27,636
再也没有比男人的荣誉感 更顽固的东西
I guess there's nothin' more pigheaded in a man than his sense of honor.

1697
02:28:29,276 --> 02:28:32,244
男人全都一个样 每个都是如此
They're all the same, every one of 'em.

1698
02:28:33,147 --> 02:28:35,171
就拿我的克里夫来说好了
You take my Cleve now.

1699
02:28:35,352 --> 02:28:37,911
他从来不肯错过任何扑克牌局
Never could turn down a poker game.

1700
02:28:38,054 --> 02:28:39,987
义无反顾一定要去
He felt duty bound to go.

1701
02:28:40,222 --> 02:28:45,056
有时还连玩三个晚上 但他就是不肯罢休…
Three nights runnin' sometimes, but he wouldn't quit, not if his life depended on it.

1702
02:28:42,956 --> 02:28:46,042
即便要他的命也一样 他…

1703
02:28:47,533 --> 02:28:49,466
我想这一点也不好笑
I guess it isn't very funny.

1704
02:28:49,536 --> 02:28:50,502
妈？
Ma!

1705
02:28:51,604 --> 02:28:52,627
爸爸呢？
Where's Pa?

1706
02:28:52,906 --> 02:28:55,430
- 他出去了 - 妈怎么了？
-Out. That's where he is. -What's the matter with Mom?

1707
02:28:55,507 --> 02:28:58,441
没事…来吧…到另一个房间
Nothin's the matter. Come on, now, in the other room.

1708
02:28:58,514 --> 02:29:00,413
- 怎么回事？ - 快点，我们想要玩！
Come on, darlin', we're gonna play.

1709
02:29:00,450 --> 02:29:02,542
乖女孩…这样才对
That's a good girl. That's better.

1710
02:29:02,584 --> 02:29:05,279
- 妈妈怎么了？ - 没怎么
-What's the matter with Mama? -Nothin's the matter.

1711
02:29:05,354 --> 02:29:06,445
你们会玩游戏吗？
You know any games?

1712
02:29:06,524 --> 02:29:08,423
- 我们会玩捉鬼 - 大风吹！
-We know tag. -Musical chairs.

1713
02:29:08,927 --> 02:29:10,359
- 捉鬼 - 我知道躲迷藏
I know hide and seek.

1714
02:29:10,629 --> 02:29:13,290
你们会玩扑克牌吗？
-Do you know how to play poker? -Poker?

1715
02:29:13,399 --> 02:29:17,391
- 扑克牌？ - 扑克牌？
You're in luck. Get down right there. Now come on, sit down. That's it.

1716
02:29:13,528 --> 02:29:17,240
算你们走运，坐下来 过来，坐下，很好

1717
02:29:17,473 --> 02:29:19,440
可是我们不会玩扑克牌
But we don't know how to play poker.

1718
02:29:19,540 --> 02:29:21,336
所以你们才要学啊
Well, it's time you learned.

1719
02:29:22,110 --> 02:29:25,135
首先，我们一人分五张牌…
First, we'll start off with a little five-card stud.

1720
02:29:44,171 --> 02:29:45,967
你的来福枪给我，齐伯
I'll take that rifle, Zeb.

1721
02:29:46,441 --> 02:29:47,964
还有你的手枪
Your pistol, too.

1722
02:29:50,980 --> 02:29:52,105
对不起，卢…
Sorry, Lou.

1723
02:29:53,217 --> 02:29:54,615
我无法照做
I just can't oblige.

1724
02:30:04,164 --> 02:30:07,155
我以为现在的法律不容许你那样做
I thought the law wouldn't let you use that any more.

1725
02:30:07,501 --> 02:30:09,229
如果必要的话 我会那么做
I'll use it if I have to.

1726
02:30:09,670 --> 02:30:12,729
我要离开这里，卢 我要带这个走
I'm goin' out of here, Lou, and I'm takin' this with me.

1727
02:30:13,510 --> 02:30:14,771
去杀葛兰特！
To kill Gant.

1728
02:30:15,278 --> 02:30:17,211
你是那么想的，是吧？
That's what you think, isn't it?

1729
02:30:17,280 --> 02:30:19,645
你以为是我和他之间的私事
It's somethin' personal between him and me.

1730
02:30:20,216 --> 02:30:22,012
卢，有可能是…
Well, Lou, it could be...

1731
02:30:22,689 --> 02:30:26,249
如果我和我的家人安定下来 等他来骚扰我们
...if I settle down with my family and wait for him to come.

1732
02:30:26,358 --> 02:30:29,190
他一定会出现的 如果我不现在阻止他的话
And he'll come, if I don't stop him here and now.

1733
02:30:30,163 --> 02:30:33,325
我要在葛兰特犯案时 人赃俱获逮住他
I'm gonna catch Gant red-handed, breakin' the law...

1734
02:30:33,701 --> 02:30:37,534
然后我要借助法律 让他永远不再得逞
...and then I'm gonna use the law to put him away once and for all.

1735
02:30:37,707 --> 02:30:39,071
法律，卢
The law, Lou.

1736
02:30:39,475 --> 02:30:41,271
我要借助法律
I'm gonna use the law...

1737
02:30:41,376 --> 02:30:44,367
但少了你的帮助 我成功的机率不大！
...but I haven't got much chance without your help.

1738
02:31:09,681 --> 02:31:11,409
守车厢里有多少人？
How many men in the caboose?

1739
02:31:11,483 --> 02:31:12,779
只有一个煞车手
Just one brakeman.

1740
02:31:13,084 --> 02:31:14,141
- 他有没有携带武器？ - 没有，从来没有
Is he armed?

1741
02:31:14,220 --> 02:31:15,584
No, never has been.

1742
02:31:16,489 --> 02:31:18,422
我会在车厢里
I'll be in the express car.

1743
02:31:24,434 --> 02:31:25,491
谢谢你，卢
Thanks.

1744
02:31:25,802 --> 02:31:26,859
骑警？
Marshal!

1745
02:31:27,137 --> 02:31:28,865
前方有几名骑士
There's some riders up ahead.

1746
02:31:30,539 --> 02:31:31,835
我来看一下
I'll take a look.

1747
02:31:52,770 --> 02:31:55,203
机师！前面有路障！
Engineer, there's a barricade ahead!

1748
02:31:55,271 --> 02:31:57,135
直接冲过去！
Open her up, wide open.

1749
02:32:23,259 --> 02:32:24,719
齐伯！

1750
02:32:24,876 --> 02:32:26,706
快点！快点！
Come on. Come on.

1751
02:32:47,839 --> 02:32:49,271
- 大家都上来了？ - 法兰奇的马跌下去了
Everybody make it?

1752
02:32:49,343 --> 02:32:50,604
- 我想他应该没上来 - 咱们开始行动吧
Frenchy's horse fell. I don't think he made it.

1753
02:32:50,677 --> 02:32:53,941
要拿到黄金还有一段路
Well, let's move. It's a long way from here to that gold.

1754
02:32:54,381 --> 02:32:56,371
没有危险，继续往前走
There's no danger. Just keep goin'.

1755
02:33:14,541 --> 02:33:15,768
是罗林
It's Rawlings!

1756
02:34:47,425 --> 02:34:48,789
火车往后退！
Back this train up!

1757
02:34:48,896 --> 02:34:49,884
快点！
And fast!

1758
02:37:11,505 --> 02:37:15,760
（旅馆）

1759
02:37:17,652 --> 02:37:19,551
我们为什么这么早就要离开，爸？
How come we're leavin' so early, Pa?

1760
02:37:19,587 --> 02:37:21,781
咱们路途遥远呢，儿子
We got a long way to go, son.

1761
02:37:22,322 --> 02:37:23,345
来
Here.

1762
02:37:27,631 --> 02:37:29,894
姨婆，我们什么时候去你家？
Auntie, when are we going to your house?

1763
02:37:29,933 --> 02:37:32,025
到你们家之后 你爸爸会再做决定
Your daddy will decide when we get to your home.

1764
02:37:32,069 --> 02:37:33,899
姨婆，可不可以带山姆一起去？
Honest? Can we take Sam with us?

1765
02:37:33,973 --> 02:37:36,099
我想是山姆带我们去吧
I think Sam is taking us.

1766
02:37:58,370 --> 02:38:01,065
爸，还有多远才到 莉莉丝姨婆的农场？
Pa, how much further is it to Aunt Lilith's ranch?

1767
02:38:01,107 --> 02:38:04,405
儿子，过下一个弯之后 再下一个弯…
Well, son, it's around the next bend, and the next bend...

1768
02:38:04,710 --> 02:38:06,233
就在山谷后面
...and the valley beyond.

1769
02:38:10,252 --> 02:38:11,809
- 莉莉丝姨婆，你知道那首歌？
Aunt Lilith, do you know that song?

1770
02:38:11,920 --> 02:38:13,284
- 那是我们的歌
That's our song!

1771
02:38:13,956 --> 02:38:15,047
你们的歌？
Your song?

1772
02:38:15,625 --> 02:38:19,287
在你爸出生之前 我早已唱过那首歌了
I sang that song long before your pa was ever born.

1773
02:38:19,799 --> 02:38:23,859
【走，走，跟我走吧】
"Away, away, come away with me

1774
02:38:24,336 --> 02:38:26,826
【那荒野长着野草】
"Where the grass grows wild

1775
02:38:26,974 --> 02:38:29,066
【这风在自由的吹】
"Where the winds blow free

1776
02:38:29,277 --> 02:38:31,642
【走，走】- 齐伯
"Away, away--" Zeb!

1777
02:38:31,746 --> 02:38:33,906
【跟我走吧】
"Come away with me

1778
02:38:34,083 --> 02:38:38,712
【我会和你在荒草上安一个家】
"Where I'll build you a home In the meadow

1779
02:38:39,256 --> 02:38:43,282
【来吧，来吧，有一片神奇的土地】
"Come, come, there's a wondrous land

1780
02:38:43,394 --> 02:38:45,827
【为了充满希望的心】
"For the hopeful heart

1781
02:38:45,930 --> 02:38:48,329
【荒野乐意帮助】
"For the willing hand

1782
02:38:48,937 --> 02:38:52,929
【来吧，来吧 ，有一片神奇的土地】
"Come, come, there's a wondrous land

1783
02:38:53,207 --> 02:38:57,404
【我将在这里为你在草地上建一个家】
"And I'll build you a home in the meadow."

1784
02:39:06,791 --> 02:39:12,228
西部就是被这些已不在人世的 先锋者，拓荒者和冒险家赢来的
The West that was won by its pioneers, settlers, adventurers is long gone now.

1785
02:39:13,366 --> 02:39:15,094
但它却永远属于他们
Yet, it is theirs forever.

1786
02:39:16,070 --> 02:39:20,165
他们在历史上留下痕迹 从未被风雨侵袭消失…
For they left tracks in history that will never be eroded by wind or rain...

1787
02:39:20,843 --> 02:39:25,336
从未被耕耘机碾平过 从未被堆肥淹没过
...never plowed under by tractors, never buried in the compost of events.

1788
02:39:27,116 --> 02:39:30,881
从他们简单纯朴的生活方式 他们强韧的生命力…
Out of the hard simplicity of their lives, out of their vitality...

1789
02:39:30,991 --> 02:39:33,151
他们的希望与悲伤…
...their hopes and their sorrows...

1790
02:39:33,726 --> 02:39:35,750
衍生出勇气与荣耀的传奇…
...grew legends of courage and pride...

1791
02:39:35,828 --> 02:39:39,024
启发他们的孩子以及后辈子孙
...to inspire their children and their children's children.

1792
02:39:40,332 --> 02:39:42,731
从他们血汗孕育过的土地…
From soil enriched by their blood...

1793
02:39:42,904 --> 02:39:45,463
和他们探索与创造的热忱…
...out of their fever to explore and build...

1794
02:39:45,909 --> 02:39:49,139
曾经炙热的沙漠如今变成大湖…
...came lakes where once were burning deserts...

1795
02:39:49,378 --> 02:39:52,972
发展出丰硕的大地 矿产以及麦田…
...came the goods of the earth, mines and wheat fields...

1796
02:39:53,084 --> 02:39:55,244
果园和伟大的伐木园…
...orchards and great lumber mills...

1797
02:39:55,520 --> 02:39:58,010
这一切便是打造这国家的力量
...all the sinews of a growing country.

1798
02:40:00,259 --> 02:40:04,092
从他们简陋的落脚之处，杂货店 演变成城市…
Out of their rude settlements, their trading posts, came cities...

1799
02:40:04,298 --> 02:40:07,061
甚至成为全世界顶尖的大城市
...to rank among the great ones of the world.

1800
02:40:07,435 --> 02:40:10,062
这一切传承让人们享有梦想的自由…
All the heritage of a people free to dream...

1801
02:40:10,838 --> 02:40:12,099
行动的自由 
...free to act...

1802
02:40:12,343 --> 02:40:14,435
让人们能自由自在开创自己的命运
...free to mold their own destiny.

1803
02:40:16,532 --> 02:40:19,501
乐土，乐土
"The promised land, promised land

1804
02:40:19,668 --> 02:40:24,401
乐土是鱼米之乡，有丰富的黄金
"Promised land The land of plenty, rich with gold

1805
02:40:24,506 --> 02:40:29,000
这里是梦想家用拳头和枪书写的
"Here came dreamers With Bible, fist and gun

1806
02:40:29,478 --> 02:40:34,347
他们的马车穿过平原的土地
"Bound for land Across the plains their wagons rode

1807
02:40:34,416 --> 02:40:36,475
抽打着皮鞭飞驰
"Hell bent for leather

1808
02:40:36,552 --> 02:40:41,012
这就是赢得西部的方式
"That's how the West was won

1809
02:40:41,723 --> 02:40:46,524
他们肩并肩驯服野蛮的大草原
"Side by side They tamed the savage prairie land

1810
02:40:46,595 --> 02:40:51,225
没有什么能阻止他们，没有风，没有雨，也没有太阳
"Nothing stopped them Nor wind, nor rain, nor sun

1811
02:40:51,466 --> 02:40:56,403
每一块土地的每一个先锋
"Side by side Each pioneer from every land

1812
02:40:56,538 --> 02:40:58,506
所有的土地都拉扯在一起
"All pulled together

1813
02:40:58,674 --> 02:41:03,043
这就是赢得西部的方式
"That's how the West was won

1814
02:41:03,378 --> 02:41:08,145
他们歌唱的时候将放下他们的脚步
"And they sang of the day When they would rest their boots

1815
02:41:08,317 --> 02:41:12,686
在这片水域流动的土地上
"In a land where the still waters flowed

1816
02:41:13,255 --> 02:41:17,851
有人有与妻子落地生根的梦想
"There were dreams of man and wife Who'd put down roots

1817
02:41:18,160 --> 02:41:22,062
他们的爱和爱的种子会在这成长
"And their love and the seeds of love Would grow

1818
02:41:32,182 --> 02:41:38,689
